#: app/data/scenario_list.py:471
msgid "4-Player Teams — 3 vs 1 with Replicators"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:479
msgid ""
"Same as 4-Player Teams 3 vs 1. The Replicator player must be on the team "
"with 3 players."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:481
msgid ""
"The setup and rules for this scenario are the same as given in the "
"4-Player Teams – 3 vs 1 scenario ([4.5]), with the following exceptions:"
"\n"
"• The Replicator player must be on the team with 3 players.\n"
"• The Replicator player draws two Empire Advantages ([MRB 10.0]) and "
"keeps one while the other two players on their team draw three Empire "
"Advantages total and each keep one."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:489
msgid "4-Player Deep Space"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:495
msgid ""
"Smaller Home Systems (14 markers per player) with 94 Deep Space markers. "
"A Deep Space-heavy map with emphasis on exploration and expansion."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:497
msgid ""
"• There are 14 Home System Markers used by each player. From their Home "
"System markers, each player selects their Homeworld, five planets, one "
"Barren Planet, and seven Mineral counters.\n"
"• Each player places their Homeworld in a hex marked with an \"H\" and "
"their remaining 13 Home System markers are mixed and placed within 3 "
"hexes of the home planet.\n"
"• The rest of the hexes get Deep Space markers — 94 will be used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:505
msgid "4-Player Three Row Deep Space"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:511
msgid ""
"25 Home System markers per player (minus one 5-Mineral). 50 Deep Space "
"markers between the quadrants. Bottom row not used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:513
msgid ""
"• There are 25 Home System markers used by each player. From their Home "
"System markers, each player removes one 5-Mineral marker, then places "
"their Homeworld in a hex marked with an \"H\" then the remaining 24 Home "
"System markers for each player are mixed and placed within the boundaries"
" shown in the diagram.\n"
"• The row of hexes at the bottom of the map do not get markers and are "
"not used.\n"
"• There are 50 Deep Space markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:521
msgid "4-Player Four Row Deep Space"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:527
msgid ""
"Same as Three Row Deep Space but with 4 rows of Deep Space. 24 Home "
"System markers per player."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:529
msgid ""
"• There are 25 Home System markers used by each player. From their Home "
"System markers, each player removes one 5-Mineral marker, then places "
"their Homeworld in a hex marked with an \"H\" then the remaining 24 Home "
"System markers for each player are mixed and placed within the "
"boundaries.\n"
"• There are 38 Deep Space markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:536
msgid "4-Player Two Maps"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:543
msgid ""
"Requires two copies of Space Empires 4X played on two boards connected by"
" their long edges. 188 Deep Space markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:545
msgid ""
"• This scenario requires two copies of Space Empires 4X and is played on "
"two boards. Twelve blank hex tiles are used to connect the two boards on "
"their long edges. If terrain is revealed during the game in one of the "
"blank hex tile spaces, the blank is removed and replaced with the "
"appropriate Terrain tile ([MRB 6.10]).\n"
"• Each player places their Homeworld in a hex marked with an \"H.\" Since"
" there are 31 Home System hexes, each player will have to use 5 of the "
"new Home system markers (marked with a \"v\" on the front side) at "
"random.\n"
"• There are 188 Deep Space markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:553
msgid "4-Player Two Maps — Corners"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:560
msgid ""
"Uses the Talon map. Each player places their Homeworld in a corner. 25 "
"Home System markers per player. 66 Deep Space markers. Partial hexes not "
"used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:562
msgid ""
"• This scenario requires the use of the map board from the game Talon, "
"also available separately through GMT Games. Each player's Homeworld is "
"placed in a hex marked with an \"H.\" The remaining 25 Home System "
"markers for each player are mixed and placed within the boundaries shown "
"in the diagram above.\n"
"• The rest of the hexes get Deep Space markers. This will use 66 of them."
"\n"
"• Partial hexes are not used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:570
msgid "4-Player Large (Talon Map)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:577
msgid ""
"Uses the Talon map with players on opposite edges. A large 4-player map "
"on a single Talon board."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:579
msgid ""
"• Setup is a slightly modified version of the 4-Player Two Maps scenario "
"([4.10]) — only add 4 new Home system markers instead of 5."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:585
msgid "4-Player — Both Talon Maps (Long Edge)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:592
msgid ""
"Two Talon boards placed long edge to long edge. 25 Home System markers "
"per player. 154 Deep Space markers. Partial hexes not used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:594
msgid ""
"• This scenario requires the use of both map boards from the game Talon, "
"also available through GMT Games. The two boards are arranged as above. "
"Each player places their Homeworld in a hex marked with an \"H\" then the"
" remaining 25 Home System markers for each player are mixed and placed "
"within the boundaries shown in the diagram above.\n"
"• There are 154 Deep Space markers.\n"
"• Partial hexes are not used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:602
msgid "4-Player — Both Talon Maps (Short Edge)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:609
msgid ""
"Slightly modified version of the Long Edge layout with boards placed "
"short edge to short edge."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:611 app/data/scenario_list.py:626
msgid ""
"• Setup is a slightly modified version of the 4-Player – Both Talon Maps "
"(Long Edge) scenario ([4.13])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:617
msgid "4-Player — Both Talon Maps (with Gaps)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:624
msgid ""
"Slightly modified version of the Long Edge layout with gaps between "
"player areas."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:632
msgid "5-Player Deep Space"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:638
msgid ""
"5-player map with 11 Home System markers per player. 95 Deep Space "
"markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:640
msgid ""
"• There are 11 Home System markers used by each player. From their Home "
"System markers, each player selects their Homeworld, five planets, one "
"Barren planet, and five Mineral counters.\n"
"• A Replicator player uses their Homeworld, four planets, one Barren "
"planet, four 10-Mineral counters, and one 5-Mineral counter.\n"
"• Each player places their Homeworld in a hex marked with an \"H\" and "
"their remaining 10 System markers are mixed and placed within two hexes "
"of the Homeworld.\n"
"• There are 95 Deep Space markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:649
msgid "5-Player Tight"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:655
msgid ""
"5-Player Deep Space map with 19 Home System markers per player. 55 Deep "
"Space markers. Tight quarters."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:657
msgid ""
"• This uses the same map as the 5-Player Deep Space scenario ([5.1]).\n"
"• There are 19 Home System markers used by each player. From their Home "
"System markers, each player selects their Homeworld, eight planets, one "
"Asteroid, one Nebula, and eight Mineral counters.\n"
"• A Replicator player uses their Homeworld, seven planets, one Barren "
"planet, two Asteroids, two Nebulae, four 10-Mineral counters, and two "
"5-Mineral counters.\n"
"• Each player places their Homeworld in a hex marked with an \"H\" then "
"the remaining 18 System markers are mixed and placed within three hexes "
"of the Homeworld.\n"
"• There are 55 Deep Space markers. When setting up this map, at least one"
" hex of Deep Space must be between each player's Home System hexes.\n"
"• There may be a turn or two where you will need to use spare numeral "
"markers to keep track of the Colony growth for all five players."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:668
msgid "5-Player Teams — 3 vs 2"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:676
msgid ""
"Uses the 5-Player Tight map and setup. Replicator must be on the 3-player"
" side."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:678
msgid ""
"• Use the same map and setup as the 5-Player Tight scenario ([5.2]).\n"
"• The Replicator Player must be part of the 3-player side.\n"
"• The 3-Player side draws no Empire Advantages ([MRB 10.0]).\n"
"• The 2-Player team draws six Empire Advantages and decides together "
"which four they will use. Each player gets the benefit of only two of the"
" cards.\n"
"• Both teams operate as an UNEASY ALLIANCE ([1.3.1])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:688
msgid "6-Player Two Row Deep Space"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:694
msgid ""
"6 players arranged in two rows of 3. Tight, aggressive map with 25 Deep "
"Space markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:696
msgid ""
"• There are 21 Home System markers used by each player, except player 5, "
"which only uses 20 Home System markers.\n"
"• From their Home System markers, each player removes two 5-Minerals, one"
" non-barren planet, one Asteroid, and one Nebula. Player 5 removes two "
"Asteroids instead of one.\n"
"• Each player places their Homeworld in a hex marked with an \"H\" then "
"the remaining 20 Home System markers (19 for player 5) for each player "
"are mixed and placed within the boundaries shown in the diagram.\n"
"• There are 25 Deep Space markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:705
msgid "6-Player Two Maps"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:712
msgid ""
"Requires two copies of Space Empires 4X. Two boards connected by their "
"long edges. 102 Deep Space markers. Partial hexes not used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:714
msgid ""
"• This scenario requires two copies of Space Empires 4X and is played on "
"two boards. Twelve blank hex tiles are used to connect the two boards on "
"their long edges. If terrain is revealed during the game in one of the "
"blank hex tile spaces, the blank is removed and replaced with the "
"appropriate Terrain tile ([MRB 6.10]).\n"
"• Twelve blank hex tiles are used to connect the two boards on their long"
" edges.\n"
"• Each player places their Homeworld in a hex marked with an \"H\" then "
"the remaining 25 Home System markers for each player are mixed and placed"
" within the boundaries shown in the diagram above.\n"
"• There are 102 Deep Space markers.\n"
"• Partial hexes are not used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:724
msgid "6-Player — Both Talon Maps"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:731
msgid ""
"Uses both Talon map boards. 3 players on each side. 102 Deep Space "
"markers. Partial hexes not used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:733
msgid ""
"• This scenario requires the use of both map boards from the game Talon, "
"also available separately through GMT Games. The two boards are arranged "
"as above, with each player's Homeworld placed in a hex marked with an "
"\"H.\" The remaining 25 Home System markers for each player are mixed and"
" placed within the boundaries shown in the diagram above.\n"
"• There are 102 Deep Space markers.\n"
"• Partial hexes are not used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:741
msgid "3-Player Quick Conquest"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:747
msgid ""
"Fast-paced 3-player conquest scenario. No Mines or Minesweepers. Uses "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Technology Head Start [g][#148][/g]</span>"
" Scenario Card. First to destroy a Homeworld wins."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:749
msgid ""
"Although the Multiplayer Short Game Victory Condition (using Colony "
"Points, 1.1.7) has been popular for providing a shorter, non-team "
"multiplayer game, the point of this game has always been conquest. These "
"scenarios are meant to provide a quicker multiplayer game with conquest "
"as the victory condition."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:751
msgid ""
"7.1 Setup\n"
"• Each player places their Homeworld in a hex marked with an \"H\" in the"
" diagrams below.\n"
"• No Mines or Minesweepers may be researched or used.\n"
"• Use the 30 CP Homeworld counters.\n"
"• Use the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Technology Head Start "
"[g][#148][/g]</span> Scenario Card (see the Card Manifest) in addition to"
" any other Scenario Cards.\n"
"• The first player to destroy a Homeworld is the winner.\n"
"• These scenarios can also be played with teams."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:763
msgid "4-Player Quick Conquest"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:769
msgid ""
"Fast-paced 4-player conquest scenario. Same rules as 3-Player Quick "
"Conquest."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:771
msgid ""
"Same rules as 3-Player Quick Conquest ([7.2]) but using the 4-Player map "
"layout. Each player places their Homeworld in a hex marked with an \"H.\""
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:777
msgid "Epic Scenarios for 2-8 Players"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:784
msgid ""
"Framework for playing with 2 to 8 players across two game boards "
"connected by Warp Points."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:786
msgid ""
"• These scenarios require two copies of the game and are played on two "
"boards (see [4.10] for how to lay out two boards).\n"
"• These are meant to enable a game with more than four players, but any "
"of the scenario set ups can be used for an epic scenario. The "
"possibilities are numerous.\n"
"  - If six players are in the game, using the 3-Player Standard set up on"
" both boards makes sense.\n"
"  - With seven players, using the 3-Player Standard setup on one board "
"and the 4-Player Standard set up on the other would work.\n"
"  - A 2-Player game can be played where each player controls an empire on"
" both maps.\n"
"  - A 4-Player game could be played with two players on each map using "
"the \"I Dare You to Play This\" set ups on both maps (in this case, it is"
" recommended that each player use all the Colony Ships of his color from "
"both games).\n"
"  - An 8-Player game could be played with a random map set up (3.2 or "
"4.2).\n"
"• Warp Points: Warp Points ([MRB 28.2]) are the connection between the "
"boards. All six Warp Point 1s (three on each board) are considered "
"connected. The same with all six Warp Point 2s. Players should agree on "
"the number of Warp Points used on each map. If the set up on a board "
"requires less than the full complement of Deep Space System markers, then"
" the number of markers needed must be counted out and the Warp Points "
"must be among them before they are randomly placed on the board.\n"
"• If more than four players are playing, then some of the same color "
"playing pieces would have to be used. There might be two green empires, "
"for example. Empires of the same color should obviously be on separate "
"maps. They are differentiated from each other by being on separate maps. "
"When a unit crosses over maps, it should be marked with a spare token.\n"
"• In an epic scenario, when one player conquers another, they add all the"
" conquered player's pieces to their build pool."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:801
msgid "2-Player Planetary Gates"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:808
msgid ""
"2-player map with pre-placed Barren Planets and Planetary Gates "
"connecting all planets within 3 hexes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:810
msgid ""
"9.1 Special Rules\n"
"9.1.1 Planetary Gates: Each planet is connected to any other planet "
"within three hexes by means of a Planetary Gate. Ground Units ([MRB "
"21.0]) on one planet may move to any other planet within three hexes via "
"this Planetary Gate. That is considered their entire move that turn. The "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Air Support [g][#25][/g]</span> Alien "
"Technology card does not enable Transports to use the Planetary Gates. "
"Colonies built on asteroids by the <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Industrious Race [g][#35][/g]</span> are not connected by "
"Planetary Gates."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:813
msgid ""
"9.1.2 Barren Planets: Barren planets may be pre-placed in deep space "
"between home systems so that it increases the likelihood that players are"
" connected by Planetary Gates. In the diagrams below, barren planets are "
"placed on the hexes marked with a \"B.\" These are suggestions for the "
"2-player, 3-player, and 4-player game. However, players should feel free "
"to play without pre-placement of planets or come up with some other "
"mutually agreed upon layout. Players may also decide to remove all Barren"
" Planets from the remaining Deep Space System markers to limit extra "
"connectivity."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:815
msgid ""
"9.1.3 Combat through Gates: If Ground Units are moved by a Planetary Gate"
" and the destination planet is colonized by another player or is a non-"
"player alien ([MRB 18.0]), ground combat occurs normally. Regardless of "
"the ground combat technology of the invading player, attacking units do "
"not get to attack in the first round. The invasion and the result are "
"handled exactly the same as if the planet was invaded from space."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:817
msgid ""
"9.1.4 Retreats: Ground Units may retreat through gates, but only to "
"friendly planets within three hexes that are free of enemy units. They "
"may retreat before bombardment or during ground combat when it is their "
"turn to fire, but not during the first round. Fighters may not retreat by"
" Planetary Gates."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:819
msgid ""
"9.1.5 Alien Planets: An NPA planet may be captured by invading through a "
"Planetary Gate. In that case, any alien ships still in orbit are removed "
"from the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:821
msgid ""
"9.1.6 Gates and Fighters: Fighters ([MRB 15.2]) may move between planets "
"like Ground Units, but only between friendly Colonies."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:823
msgid ""
"9.1.7 Colony Ships: When a Colony Ship is purchased, it may be purchased "
"as a non-spacefaring Colony Ship. It still costs the same, but it can be "
"placed, without the use of a SY, on any Colony that produced 5 CP in that"
" Economic Phase. It should be placed ship-side-up on top of the existing "
"Colony. A non-spacefaring Colony Ship can never move into space but may "
"travel through Planetary Gates like ground units. It must colonize the "
"first uncolonized planet that it moves to. The ship is left on the "
"uncolonized planet and is flipped in the Economic Phase just as it would "
"be if it was a normal Colony Ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:825
msgid ""
"Similar to space combat, the Colony Ship may enter a hex with enemy units"
" only when accompanied by friendly ground units, may not retreat, and is "
"destroyed if the enemy wins the combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:827
msgid ""
"Design Note: Just when you think you don't need ships any more, that "
"fleet shows up and starts wasting your Colonies from space. Then when you"
" let your guard down on the ground, an invasion force shows up in your "
"Home System and starts spreading from planet to planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:833
msgid "3-Player Planetary Gates"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:840
msgid ""
"3-player version of Planetary Gates with Barren Planets pre-placed "
"between all three empires."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:842
msgid ""
"Same Planetary Gate rules as the 2-Player version ([9.1]). 3-player map "
"with Barren Planets pre-placed on hexes marked \"B\" between all three "
"empires."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:848
msgid "4-Player Planetary Gates"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:855
msgid ""
"4-player version of Planetary Gates with Barren Planets pre-placed in the"
" center of the map."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:857
msgid ""
"Same Planetary Gate rules as the 2-Player version ([9.1]). 4-player map "
"with Barren Planets pre-placed on hexes marked \"B\" in the center and "
"between empires."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:863
msgid "2-Player Space Amoebas"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:870
msgid ""
"Standard 2-player map with Space Amoebas pre-placed between the two "
"empires."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:872
msgid ""
"10.0 Space Amoeba Scenarios\n"
"Giant Space Amoebas can be added to many of the competitive scenarios in "
"this book. During the game, the Space Amoebas will multiply and attempt "
"to destroy the human players. There are similar rules for Space Amoebas "
"included in the Solo/Co-Op Scenario Book ([SSB 3.0])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:875
msgid ""
"10.1 Setup\n"
"• Space Amoebas may be pre-placed in Deep Space between the Home Systems."
" No Deep Space marker is placed in a hex with an Amoeba.\n"
"• In the diagrams to follow, Space Amoebas are placed on the hexes marked"
" with an \"S\" as suggestions. Players should feel free to play with some"
" other mutually agreed upon layout.\n"
"• All Space Amoebas are of one type (unless the players agree upon "
"multiple types). A Space Amoeba counter of any of the three included "
"types may be used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:880
msgid ""
"10.2 Special Rules\n"
"• Unlike the solitary Space Amoeba scenario there are no rule "
"restrictions (i.e., Titans, Ground Combat, Facilities, etc. can be used)."
"\n"
"• Unlike the solitary Space Amoeba scenario players must pay maintenance "
"as usual.\n"
"• Unlike the solitary Space Amoeba scenario Barren Planets do have Non-"
"Player Aliens ([MRB 18.0]) on them.\n"
"• Minesweepers (SW) represent Science Vessels (SV) and pull double duty. "
"Minesweeper technology also counts as Science and must be researched to "
"produce hybrid Minesweeper/Science Vessels. A Minesweeper counter may "
"both research Amoebas and sweep Mines.\n"
"• Only the first two levels of Minesweeper technology count as Science "
"technology. Minesweeper 3 does not provide additional research bonus.\n"
"• If a player is eliminated by an Amoeba, play continues for remaining "
"players."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:888
msgid ""
"10.3 Researching Space Amoebas\n"
"• Until a player has researched the Amoebas, they cannot be attacked and "
"will destroy all that player's ships (except SVs) in the same hex.\n"
"• Unlike the solitaire scenario, a player is not required to lose a ship "
"before researching.\n"
"• Each player must research individually.\n"
"• Research Points carry over from turn to turn.\n"
"• Each turn an SV is in a hex with an Amoeba, roll dice:\n"
"  1-2: Two Research Points gained.\n"
"  3-5: One Research Point gained.\n"
"  6-8: Nothing.\n"
"  9-10: SV destroyed.\n"
"• Level 1 SVs roll one die. Level 2 SVs roll two dice, take the best.\n"
"• Level 2 can't be acquired until Level 1 SV has researched an Amoeba.\n"
"• Once a player has 10 Research Points, they may attack any Amoeba for "
"the rest of the game.\n"
"• After 10 RP, Amoebas no longer automatically destroy ships. Combat "
"ensues as normal. Science Vessels never participate in combat with an "
"Amoeba."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:903
msgid ""
"10.4 Space Amoeba Strength\n"
"After 10 RP, the player has figured out how to kill the Amoebas. No "
"retrofit needed ([MRB 9.11.3])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:906
msgid ""
"10.4.1 Determine Amoeba Strength: The first player to gather 10 RP rolls "
"on the Amoeba Strength Table. This result applies to all players but "
"should not be revealed until others complete their own research."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:908
msgid ""
"10.5 Amoeba Strength Table\n"
"Roll 1: C7-1-1\n"
"Roll 2: D6-2-2\n"
"Roll 3: A7-2-2. Also vulnerable to fighters.\n"
"Roll 4: A7-2-2. Becomes A5-1-2 when faced by ONLY Raiders.\n"
"Roll 5: B5-1-2. Two attacks each round. Each may lead to Chain Attack "
"([10.6.3]).\n"
"Roll 6-7: A7-2-2. If 3+ different ship types attacking, all get +1 "
"Attack.\n"
"Roll 8-10: Can only be killed by detonating a ship inside. "
"CA/BC/BB/DN/Titan = auto-destroy. DD/MB = destroyed on 1-8. SC = "
"destroyed on 1-4. Ship attempting this is always destroyed. If Amoeba "
"survives, other ships in hex are destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:917
msgid ""
"10.6 Amoeba Properties\n"
"• All Amoebas have Tactics Level 2.\n"
"• All Amoebas are immune to Cloaking and Fighters unless otherwise "
"specified.\n"
"• Ships never get Fleet Size Bonus ([MRB 5.1.3]) against Amoebas."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:922
msgid ""
"10.6.1 Amoeba Target Priority: Roll a die. 1-5 = attack smallest ship (by"
" CP). 6-10 = attack largest. Flagships considered highest CP. Ties chosen"
" by player."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:924
msgid ""
"10.6.2 Amoeba Attack Procedure: Rolls one die, comparing Attack Strength "
"to Defense Strength (including tech). Hull Size 2 ships get +1 Defense. "
"Hull Size 3+ get +2 Defense. Successful attack = swallowed regardless of "
"size. Roll of 1 always succeeds."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:926
msgid ""
"10.6.3 Chain Attacks: If Amoeba swallows a ship and rolls 2 or less than "
"needed, it immediately attacks again. Can happen any number of times per "
"round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:928
msgid "10.6.4 Amoeba Healing: Healed same way as ships after combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:930
msgid ""
"10.7 Spreading of Space Amoebas\n"
"Amoebas never move. They spread at the start of the Economic Phase before"
" purchases."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:933
msgid ""
"10.7.1 Spread Procedure:\n"
"• Do not start spreading until Economic Phase 7 (or by mutual agreement)."
"\n"
"• Only one Amoeba per hex.\n"
"• Each Amoeba spreads one time per Economic Phase.\n"
"• In turn order, each player picks an Amoeba and chooses its spread hex.\n"
"• If it can spread onto a planet, it must.\n"
"• Newly placed Amoebas do not spread that phase.\n"
"• Amoebas never spread outside the scenario map area.\n"
"• Space Amoebas will not spread into a DM hex and DMs will not enter "
"Amoeba hexes.\n"
"• Not limited by counter mix. Use substitutions."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:944
msgid ""
"10.7.2 Contact with Ships: If ships in hex where Amoeba spreads, special "
"combat round occurs immediately. If player has not gathered 10 RP, all "
"non-SV ships destroyed. Amoebas automatically destroy NPA ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:946
msgid ""
"10.7.3 Contact with System Markers: Amoeba removes System marker in any "
"hex it spreads to (after defeating ships). Will not spread into Black "
"Holes or Supernovas. Skip Folds in Space. Otherwise unaffected by System "
"markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:948
msgid ""
"10.8 Space Amoebas and Mines\n"
"Mines hinder spreading but don't affect Amoebas like ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:951
msgid ""
"10.8.1 Procedure: If only a Mine (or Mine + SV) in same hex, no combat. "
"Mine removed in Economic Phase, Amoeba doesn't spread that phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:953
msgid ""
"10.8.2 Contact with Mines: Amoebas may spread onto Mines normally. Mines "
"remain in hex until next Economic Phase when they may stop spreading."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:955
msgid ""
"10.8.3 Adapting to Mines: Once per Economic Phase an Amoeba doesn't "
"spread due to a Mine, roll a die. On 9-10, Amoebas are no longer "
"prevented from spreading by Mines in future phases. Place \"No Mine\" "
"counter as reminder."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:957
msgid ""
"10.9 2-Player Space Amoebas\n"
"Space Amoebas are placed on the hexes marked with an \"S\" on the Large "
"2-Player Map."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:961
msgid "3 A7-2-2. The Amoebas are also vulnerable to fighters."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:962
msgid ""
"5 B5-1-2. The Amoebas have voracious appetites and gets two attacks each "
"round. Each of these attacks may lead to a Chain Attack ([10.6.3])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:963
msgid ""
"8-10 The Amoebas can only be killed by detonating a ship inside them. "
"Only one ship may attempt this per turn. If the ship is a CA, BC, BB, DN,"
" or Titan, the Amoeba is destroyed. If the ship is a DD or MB the Amoeba "
"is destroyed on a roll of 1-8 and if the ship is a SC the Amoeba is "
"destroyed on a roll of 1-4. In all cases, the ship attempting this is "
"destroyed. Only the ships listed here can be used. If the Amoeba "
"survives, other ships in the hex with the Amoeba are destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:966 app/data/scenario_list.py:1387
msgid ""
"Design Note: Yes, I know it says SW on the counters, but in this "
"scenario, it is also as if they say SV, as in Science Vessels. Pretend "
"that the SW was put on the counter by someone who heard the words "
"“Science Vessel” spoken by someone with a bad TV Russian accent (I’m "
"looking at you, Chekov)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:967
msgid ""
"i Design Note: In sci-fi terms, the Amoeba can be killed if the player "
"slightly tweaks their weapons – by adjusting the frequency to the upper "
"EM band, by adjusting the phase, by reversing the polarity, or by doing "
"something else pseudo-scientific sounding. The specific adjustment is not"
" important. It means it is now possible to (immediately) attack them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:973
msgid "3-Player Space Amoebas"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:980
msgid "Standard 3-player map with Space Amoebas pre-placed in the center."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:982 app/data/scenario_list.py:1000
msgid ""
"Same Space Amoeba rules as section [10.0]-[10.8] (see csb_sa_2p for full "
"rules)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:984
msgid ""
"10.10 3-Player Space Amoebas\n"
"Space Amoebas are placed on the hexes marked with an \"S\" on the "
"Standard 3-Player Map."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:991
msgid "4-Player Space Amoebas"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:998
msgid ""
"Standard 4-player map with Space Amoebas pre-placed in the center of the "
"map."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1002
msgid ""
"10.11 4-Player Space Amoebas\n"
"Space Amoebas are placed on the hexes marked with an \"S\" on the "
"Standard 4-Player Map."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1009
msgid "King of the Warp Point"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1016
msgid ""
"Alternate victory scenario. Players score VPs by having Science Vessels "
"at Warp Points each Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1018
msgid ""
"The Warp Points are the key to victory in this scenario. They represent "
"access to vast scientific treasures and ancient civilizations. By "
"studying them, players unlock knowledge that will lead them to make "
"galaxy changing advances."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1020
msgid ""
"11.1.1 Setup: Before the Deep Space markers are placed on the map, the "
"Warp Points are taken out of the mix. Depending on the scenario, a number"
" of Warp Points are placed in mutually agreed upon hexes in the Deep "
"Space portion of the map. Some guidelines on Warp Point placement:\n"
"• It is strongly suggested that you use either:\n"
"  - One Warp Point, or\n"
"  - One less Warp Point than the number of players, or\n"
"  - One more Warp Point than the number of players.\n"
"• All of the Warp Points can be placed centrally, or one could be placed "
"to the advantage of each player with an extra one in the middle. There "
"are a lot of options, and each will change the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1027
msgid ""
"Design Note: Each of the above will make for a very different and "
"interesting game — is it important to hold one Warp Point or do I need to"
" hold several?"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1029
msgid ""
"If the players cannot agree on the placement of the Warp Points, then one"
" player should place all the Warp Points while the other players choose "
"their starting positions after he does."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1031
msgid ""
"Unused Warp Points should be placed to the side and not mixed in with the"
" rest of the Deep Space Markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1033
msgid ""
"11.1.2 Warp Point Properties: None of the Warp Points in this scenario "
"are connected. Their only purpose is to provide VPs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1035
msgid ""
"11.1.3 Minesweepers: These ships have a dual function in this scenario. "
"They not only sweep Mines, but also act as Science Vessels. You must "
"still research Mine Sweeping Technology to build SWs ([MRB 17.2])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1037
msgid ""
"11.1.4 Game Length: Players should decide at the start of the game how "
"many Economic Phases they want the game to last. The game ends after that"
" Economic Phase. 10-12 Economic turns are good for a shorter game, "
"depending on the scenario. This scenario also works with a longer, 15-20 "
"Economic Phase game, although players in that one will have to be careful"
" not to become too focused on the Warp Points as it will become more and "
"more likely that someone will launch a game winning attack against a "
"Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1039
msgid ""
"11.1.5 Victory Points: Players score 1 VP during the Economic Phase for "
"each Warp Point that shares a hex with one or more of their Science "
"Vessels in the same hex as a Warp Point. All Science Vessels must be "
"revealed during the Economic Phase. The player with the most VPs at the "
"end of the agreed upon number of Economic Phases is the winner. In the "
"event of a tie, after the purchases for the Economic Phase are completed,"
" the players add up the CP value of all combat capable ships they have on"
" the board and the winner is the player whose fleet adds up to the most "
"CP. In the event of another tie, the tied players share the win."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1041
msgid ""
"11.1.6 Alternate Point Scoring: As a twist to this scenario, players can "
"agree that they will score 1 VP per Science Vessel at a Warp Point in the"
" Economic Phase. This will change the scenario strategy significantly "
"(weighing combat capability versus number of Science Vessels is tough) "
"and it is recommended that you play this version only with one Warp "
"Point."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1047
msgid "Grab the Artifacts"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1053
msgid ""
"Alternate victory scenario. Ancient artifacts in Deep Space must be "
"gathered by Miners and delivered for VPs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1055
msgid ""
"Ancient artifacts of great value litter Deep Space and players must "
"gather and study them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1057
msgid ""
"11.2.1 Setup: Extra pieces or counters will be needed for this scenario "
"(pieces from an old Risk game will work well). One of these extra pieces "
"is placed in every Deep Space hex (along with the exploration marker). "
"These will represent the ancient artifacts."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1059
msgid ""
"11.2.2 Exploring Artifacts: After exploration, artifacts remain in the "
"hex even if the System marker is removed (Danger!, etc.). Exception: "
"Artifacts in Supernovas ([MRB 6.5]), Folds In Space ([MRB 25.2]), and "
"Quantum Filaments ([MRB 25.5]) are removed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1061
msgid ""
"11.2.3 Moving Artifacts: Artifacts may only be moved by Miners. Place the"
" artifact on the Miner counter when a Miner picks it up. They may pick up"
" an artifact at any point during their move. The following rules apply to"
" moving artifacts:\n"
"• Each Miner may carry only one artifact at a time and may not carry "
"minerals or Space Wrecks at the same time.\n"
"• Artifacts being towed by Miners are destroyed if the Miner is "
"destroyed.\n"
"• Miners may drop off artifacts at their Homeworld or at a Colony that is"
" connected by MS Pipelines to the Homeworld (it is assumed a civilian "
"ship is able to transport the artifact from there). Miners may not drop "
"off artifacts at Colonies that are not yet connected in this way."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1066
msgid ""
"11.2.4 Victory Conditions: Each artifact dropped off is worth 1 VP. The "
"game ends immediately the instant it is dropped off (even in the middle "
"of a turn) once someone has scored enough VPs that there is no possible "
"way that their total may be passed by another player given the artifacts "
"remaining on the board. In the event of a tie, the person who achieved "
"their Victory Point total first is declared the winner."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1069
msgid ""
"Design Note: Each of the above will make for a very different and "
"interesting game – is it important to hold one Warp Point or do I need to"
" hold several?"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1075
msgid "Standing Ships Variant"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1081
msgid "Physical variant using plastic stands for unrevealed ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1083
msgid ""
"The following variants add the use of plastic stands which either provide"
" more access to information or add an additional element of hidden "
"information to the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1085
msgid ""
"• Unrevealed ships are not placed face down as in the normal game. "
"Instead, ships are placed upright in stands facing the owning player.\n"
"• The number of ships in each group is tracked on the Ship Technology "
"Sheet.\n"
"• When a group is revealed, it is placed face up and a numeral marker "
"placed underneath.\n"
"• Groups still have a limit of six ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1091
#, python-format
msgid ""
"12.0 Taking A Stand (2-Player Variant) The following variants add the use"
" of plastic stands which either provide more access to information or add"
" an additional element of hidden information to the game. 12.1 STANDING "
"SHIPS VARIANT • Unrevealed ships are not placed face down as in the "
"normal game. Instead, ships are placed upright in stands facing the "
"player. • The number of ships in each group is tracked on the Ship "
"Technology Sheet. • When a group is revealed, it is placed face up and a "
"numeral marker placed underneath. • Groups still have a limit of six "
"ships. 12.2 2-PLAYER HIDDEN EXPLORATION VARIANT 12.2.1 Changes to "
"Exploration • The map is set up normally, with face down System markers. "
"• Deep Space markers must be explored by both sides. When a Deep Space "
"System marker is explored or would be returned face up with Exploration "
"technology ([MRB 9.8]) for the first time, it is not flipped face up and "
"it may not be left face down. Instead, it is placed upright in a stand "
"facing the exploring player. Some markers will be facing one player and "
"some the other, depending on who explored it. If a marker is explored by "
"the other player, it is then removed from the stand and placed face up. "
"All markers that have been explored by both players will be face up on "
"the board. • When a Deep Space System marker is explored by a ship for "
"the first time, a Decoy ([MRB 8.3]) may be added to the hex. Players may "
"scuttle another decoy during the exploration phase to accommodate this. "
"After looking at the System marker and placing it in a stand, the player "
"removes either the Decoy or the exploring ship. There will be one marker "
"left in the hex, but the other player will not know whether it is a Decoy"
" or a ship and therefore will be less likely to know if the Exploration "
"went well. - If the System marker indicates that the hex is safe, the "
"player removes the Decoy. - If the System marker indicates the ship’s "
"destruction, the player removes the ship. 12.2.2 Special Rules • Deep "
"Space Black Holes ([MRB 6.3]) are 100% deadly until explored by both "
"players. If not face up or in a stand, a Deep Space Black Hole will "
"always suck in the first exploring ship(s) (no need to roll the die). "
"When this occurs, the Decoy marker is left behind. Future ships entering "
"the hex roll the die as normal (which will give"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1092
#, python-format
msgid ""
"away that this is a Black Hole) • Alien planets ([MRB 18.0]) are also "
"100% deadly if attacked by a lone ship. The first time an alien planet is"
" discovered and placed in a stand, it is treated like a Danger! marker "
"and the exploring ship is removed without die rolls (leaving the Decoy "
"marker behind). NPA ships are not chosen and placed in the hex until both"
" sides have explored the planet or it is attacked by more than one ship. "
"• Lost in Space markers ([MRB 6.6]) are treated like Danger! markers when"
" first explored. Future ships from the same player entering the hex later"
" ignore the effect. • Space Pirates ([MRB 25.7]) are turned face up and "
"handled normally. • Regional Maps ([MRB 25.6]) are turned face up and "
"handled normally (which could cause adjacent markers to be put in "
"stands). • Minerals ([MRB 6.7]) and Space Wrecks ([MRB 6.8]) are placed "
"in stands. However, if that player sends a Miner into the hex, it can be "
"removed from the stand and picked up normally. • Supernovas ([MRB 6.5]) "
"are treated like Danger! markers ([MRB 6.4]) when first explored. If "
"explored by a ship, the Decoy is left behind in the hex and must be moved"
" out during the next turn. It is possible that this could cause a Decoy "
"to pass through a Supernova and out the other side under this one "
"exception. The player that has explored the Supernova may not send ships "
"into the hex. • Folds In Space ([MRB 25.2]) have no effect when first "
"explored, remove the Decoy. Future ships may either enter the hex and "
"ignore the usual effects or move through it. Once a ship moves through it"
" remove the marker from the stand and place it face up. • Quantum "
"Filaments ([MRB 25.5]) are treated like Danger! markers when first "
"explored. Future ships from the same player may enter, but must spend an "
"extra movement hex as normal. • Note that a player may ignore beneficial "
"terrain effects (e.g. Pulsars [MRB 25.4]) to keep the terrain tile hidden"
" from their opponent. 12.2.3 Game Effects • This variant creates paths "
"that can be easily traversed by one player (because they’ve explored it),"
" but not the other. That will at times allow a fleet to more easily "
"retreat or avoid combat. • Both players are more likely to research "
"Exploration technology because they will not be able to easily use a path"
" made by the other player. • The cost of suffering a bad exploration "
"result is slightly less because the player will receive a Decoy as a "
"result. • There will be more Decoys on the board."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1098
msgid "2-Player Hidden Exploration Variant"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1104
msgid ""
"Physical variant using stands for System markers. Deep Space markers must"
" be explored by both sides."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1106
msgid ""
"12.2.1 Changes to Exploration\n"
"• The map is set up normally, with face down System markers.\n"
"• Deep Space markers must be explored by both sides. When a Deep Space "
"System marker is explored or would be returned face up with Exploration "
"technology ([MRB 9.8]) for the first time, it is not flipped face up and "
"it may not be left face down. Instead, it is placed upright in a stand "
"facing the exploring player. Some markers will be facing one player and "
"some the other, depending on who explored it. If a marker is explored by "
"the other player, it is then removed from the stand and placed face up. "
"All markers that have been explored by both players will be face up on "
"the board.\n"
"• When a Deep Space System marker is explored by a ship for the first "
"time, a Decoy ([MRB 8.3]) may be added to the hex. Players may scuttle "
"another decoy during the exploration phase to accommodate this. After "
"looking at the System marker and placing it in a stand, the player "
"removes either the Decoy or the exploring ship. There will be one marker "
"left in the hex, but the other player will not know whether it is a ship "
"or a Decoy and therefore will be less likely to know if the Exploration "
"went well.\n"
"  - If the System marker indicates that the hex is safe, the player "
"removes the Decoy.\n"
"  - If the System marker indicates the ship's destruction, the player "
"removes the ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1113
#, python-format
msgid ""
"12.2.2 Special Rules\n"
"• Deep Space Black Holes ([MRB 6.3]) are 100% deadly until explored by "
"both players. If not face up or in a stand, a Deep Space Black Hole will "
"always suck in the first exploring ship(s) (no need to roll the die). "
"When this occurs, the Decoy marker is left behind. Future ships entering "
"the hex roll the die as normal (which will give away that this is a Black"
" Hole).\n"
"• Alien planets ([MRB 18.0]) are also 100% deadly if attacked by a lone "
"ship. The first time an alien planet is discovered and placed in a stand,"
" it is treated like a Danger! marker and the exploring ship is removed "
"without die rolls (leaving the Decoy marker behind). NPA ships are not "
"chosen and placed on the planet until both sides have explored the planet"
" or it is attacked by more than one ship.\n"
"• Lost in Space markers ([MRB 6.6]) are treated like Danger! markers when"
" first explored. Future ships from the same player entering the hex later"
" ignore the effect.\n"
"• Space Pirates ([MRB 25.7]) are turned face up and handled normally.\n"
"• Regional Maps ([MRB 25.6]) are turned face up and handled normally "
"(which could cause adjacent markers to be put in stands).\n"
"• Minerals ([MRB 6.7]) and Space Wrecks ([MRB 6.8]) are placed in stands."
" However, if that player sends a Miner into the hex, it can be removed "
"from the stand and picked up normally.\n"
"• Supernovas ([MRB 6.5]) are treated like Danger! markers when first "
"explored. If explored by a ship, the Decoy is left behind in the hex and "
"must be moved out during the next turn. It is possible that this could "
"cause a Decoy to pass through a Supernova and out the other side under "
"this one exception. The player that has explored the Supernova may not "
"send ships into the hex.\n"
"• Folds in Space ([MRB 25.2]) have no effect when first explored, remove "
"the Decoy. Future ships may either enter the hex and ignore the usual "
"effects or move through it. Once a ship moves through it remove the "
"marker from the stand and place it face up.\n"
"• Quantum Filaments ([MRB 25.5]) are treated like Danger! markers when "
"first explored. Future ships from the same player may enter, but must "
"spend an extra movement hex as normal.\n"
"• Note that a player may ignore beneficial terrain effects (e.g. Pulsars "
"[MRB 25.4]) to keep the terrain tile hidden from their opponent."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1125
msgid ""
"12.2.3 Game Effects\n"
"• This variant creates paths that can be easily traversed by one player "
"(because they've explored it), but not the other. That will at times "
"allow a fleet to more easily retreat or avoid combat.\n"
"• Both players are more likely to research Exploration technology because"
" they will not be able to easily use a path made by the other player.\n"
"• The cost of suffering a bad exploration result is slightly less because"
" the player will receive a Decoy as a result.\n"
"• There will be more Decoys on the board."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1135
msgid "Doomsday Machines Solitaire (Scenarios 1 & 2)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1143
msgid ""
"An evil race sends Doomsday Machines toward your growing empire. Two map "
"sizes available: Small (Deep Space within 2 hexes of Home System, 3 DMs) "
"and Large (Deep Space within 4 hexes, 3 DMs at higher starting strength)."
" Facilities limited to IC and RC only."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1145
msgid ""
"2.0 1-Player Doomsday Machine Scenarios\n"
"An evil race is sending \"Doomsday Machines\" towards your growing empire!"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1148
msgid ""
"2.1 Setup\n"
"• There are 26 Home System markers for the player. The 30 CP Homeworld "
"should be placed in the hex with the \"H.\"\n"
"• There is no need for a turn order bid. The player always takes their "
"turn before the DMs unless 1.1.10 is used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1152
msgid ""
"2.2 Special Rules\n"
"Only the following Advanced/Optional Rules may be used in this scenario:\n"
"• MS Pipelines ([MRB 13.0]).\n"
"• Carriers, Fighters, & Point Defense ([MRB 15.0]).\n"
"• Raiders ([MRB 16.0]).\n"
"• Mines & Minesweepers ([MRB 17.0]).\n"
"• Optional Deep Space Discoveries ([MRB 28.0]).\n"
"• Instant Technology Upgrade ([MRB 30.0]).\n"
"• Black Hole Slingshot ([MRB 31.0]).\n"
"• Research Gearing Limits ([MRB 32.0]).\n"
"• Unpredictable Research ([MRB 33.0]).\n"
"• Facilities (IC & RC only, [MRB 36.0])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1165
msgid ""
"2.2.1 Victory Conditions: The player wins by defeating all of the "
"Doomsday Machines (DMs) sent at them and loses if their Homeworld is "
"destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1167
msgid ""
"2.3 Doomsday Machine Details\n"
"Doomsday Machines are massive battle stations capable of destroying "
"entire planets."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1170
msgid ""
"2.3.1 Arrival Times: The DMs appear at the end of the Economic Phase "
"specified on the scenario's Doomsday Machine Difficulty Table ([2.7], "
"[2.8])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1172
msgid ""
"2.3.2 Arrival Locations: Map hexes marked with red numbers represent DM "
"entry points. When a DM arrives, roll a die to determine in which hex it "
"appears."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1174
msgid ""
"2.3.3 Movement Guidelines: DMs always move towards the closest player "
"Colony. If two Colonies are equidistant, then a DM will always move "
"toward the Colony that is larger (in CP). If more than one equidistant "
"Colonies are the same size, then the DM will move towards the Colony that"
" brings it closest to the player's Homeworld. If it is still tied, then "
"it is the player's choice. As a DM moves toward a Colony, if two "
"different hexes will put it equidistant from the target Colony, it will "
"move toward the hex that is also closer to the player's Homeworld. Each "
"time a DM moves, its target Colony may change. The player may not reduce "
"a Colony or remove it in order to change the direction of a DM."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1176
msgid ""
"2.3.4 Strength and Weaknesses: Each map contains a table indicating what "
"Economic Phase each DM enters play and the DM Rating row to use for that "
"DM's statistics (Table 2.5). When DMs enter play, roll 1d10. The DM "
"appears in the matching red-numbered hex on the scenario map. When that "
"DM is first encountered, its weakness is determined by rolling a die and "
"consulting the Doomsday Machine Weakness Table ([2.6])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1178
msgid ""
"2.3.5 Movement Rate: DMs always move one hex per turn and may not use "
"Warp Points ([MRB 28.2]). Unlike in multiplayer games, DMs can move in a "
"hex with an unexplored marker and when it does, do NOT flip the marker."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1180
msgid ""
"2.3.6 System Markers and DMs: DMs are unaffected by System markers (see "
"exceptions in [2.3.7] and [2.3.8]). A player may not move into a hex with"
" a DM and an unexplored System marker. If you wanted to move there you "
"should have explored it before the DM got there!"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1182
msgid ""
"2.3.7 Special Combat Conditions: A DM's Attack/Defense Strengths are not "
"affected by Asteroids or Nebulae. DMs are affected by Ion Storms ([MRB "
"25.1.3]) and Quasars ([MRB 5.8]). Unlike multiplayer games, DMs do not "
"destroy Asteroids in solitaire scenarios ([MRB 29.4])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1184
msgid ""
"2.3.8 Planets and Colonies: If a DM is in a hex with a planet (with or "
"without a Colony), it will destroy that planet. Remove the planet and any"
" Colony from play. The DM must first defeat any defending ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1186
msgid ""
"2.4 Doomsday Machine Combat Rules\n"
"• If a DM moves into a hex with the player's ships, it will engage them "
"in combat.\n"
"• Unless specified as a weakness, all DMs are immune to Mines, Fighters "
"(their weaponry is too small to affect them), and Cloaking (they are "
"equipped with the highest level of Scanners).\n"
"• The player does not get the Fleet Size Bonus ([MRB 5.1.3]) for "
"outnumbering a DM.\n"
"• A roll of 1 is not an automatic hit on a DM. However, a roll of 1 by a "
"DM is always a hit. A DM that rolls a 10 is always a miss.\n"
"• DMs carry damage from combat to combat (they do not automatically "
"heal). However, they do heal two damage instantly every time they destroy"
" a planet (whether or not it has a Colony).\n"
"• DMs get more than one attack per round as shown on the table ([2.5]). "
"All attacks are of the same strength and occur at the same time. A DM is "
"considered to have Tactics 2.\n"
"• The player should use common sense when allocating the attacks of a DM."
" If weak against Fighters, it should target Fighters. If weak against "
"large fleets, it should attack smaller ships or damaged ships in order to"
" get the fleet size under 10, etc. Like with human players, DMs may roll "
"their attacks one at a time and see the result before rolling more "
"attacks.\n"
"• A DM never retreats from combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1196
msgid ""
"2.5 Doomsday Machine Strength\n"
"DM Rating 1: Attack D7, Defense 1, Hull Size 6, Attacks 3\n"
"DM Rating 2: Attack C7, Defense 1, Hull Size 7, Attacks 4\n"
"DM Rating 3: Attack C8, Defense 2, Hull Size 7, Attacks 4\n"
"DM Rating 4: Attack C8, Defense 2, Hull Size 8, Attacks 4\n"
"DM Rating 5: Attack B9, Defense 2, Hull Size 8, Attacks 5\n"
"DM Rating 6: Attack B9, Defense 3, Hull Size 9, Attacks 5\n"
"DM Rating 7: Attack B10, Defense 3, Hull Size 9, Attacks 6\n"
"DM Rating 8: Attack A10, Defense 3, Hull Size 10, Attacks 6\n"
"DM Rating 9: Attack A11, Defense 4, Hull Size 10, Attacks 6\n"
"DM Rating 10: Attack A11, Defense 4, Hull Size 11, Attacks 6"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1208
msgid ""
"2.6 Doomsday Machine Weakness\n"
"Die Roll 1-2 — Fighters: Fighters can fire and damage a DM normally.\n"
"Die Roll 3-4 — Mines: Each Mine will cause a hit on a DM on a roll of "
"1-5.\n"
"Die Roll 5-6 — Cloaking: Raiders fire as A-Class instead of D-Class in "
"every round and have a +1 Attack Strength bonus in the first round. In "
"addition, this DM gets -2 on its Attack Strength when firing at Raiders."
"\n"
"Die Roll 7-8 — Large Fleets: Player will get the Fleet Size Bonus in any "
"round in which they attack the DM with at least 10 ships (that can hit "
"the DM).\n"
"Die Roll 9-10 — None."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1215
msgid ""
"2.7 Doomsday Machines – Small (Solitaire Scenario 1)\n"
"• Deep Space markers are placed within two hexes of the player's Home "
"System areas, except that a marker is not placed in any of the possible "
"DM entry hexes. The player may not enter these hexes.\n"
"• The player will face a total of three DMs. Each enters at the start of "
"the Economic Phase at the Rating according to the table below.\n"
"• \"#/#\" – The first number is the Economic Phase the DM enters. The "
"second number is the DM Rating.\n"
"Difficulty Table (Small):\n"
"Easy: First DM 7/1, Second DM 9/3, Third DM 11/5\n"
"Normal: First DM 7/2, Second DM 9/4, Third DM 10/6\n"
"Hard: First DM 6/1, Second DM 8/3, Third DM 10/5\n"
"Harder: First DM 6/2, Second DM 8/4, Third DM 9/6\n"
"Good Luck!: First DM 5/1, Second DM 7/3, Third DM 9/5"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1226
msgid ""
"2.8 Doomsday Machines – Large (Solitaire Scenario 2)\n"
"• Deep Space markers are placed within four hexes of the player's Home "
"System areas, except that a marker is not placed in any of the possible "
"DM entry hexes. The player may not enter these hexes.\n"
"• The player will face a total of three DMs. Each enters at the start of "
"the Economic Phase at the Attack Strength according to the table below.\n"
"• \"#/#\" – The first number is the Economic Phase the DM enters. The "
"second number is the DM Rating.\n"
"Difficulty Table (Large):\n"
"Easy: First DM 8/5, Second DM 10/7, Third DM 12/9\n"
"Normal: First DM 8/6, Second DM 10/8, Third DM 11/10\n"
"Hard: First DM 7/5, Second DM 9/7, Third DM 11/9\n"
"Harder: First DM 7/6, Second DM 9/8, Third DM 10/10\n"
"Good Luck!: First DM 6/5, Second DM 8/7, Third DM 10/9"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1238 app/data/scenario_list.py:1955
msgid "1-2 Fighters: Fighters can fire and damage a DM normally."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1239 app/data/scenario_list.py:1956
msgid ""
"5-6 Cloaking: Raiders fire as A-Class instead of D-Class in every round "
"and have a +1 Attack Strength bonus in the first round. In addition, this"
" DM gets -2 on its Attack Strength when firing at Raiders."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1242
msgid ""
"PLAY NOTE: In coop games versus two or more Alien Players, the APs may "
"also stack their units defensively and may attack simultaneously, if "
"able."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1248
msgid "Doomsday Machines — Hidden Galactic Capitol"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1255
msgid ""
"Variant for DM solitaire scenarios. An ancient Galactic Capitol is hidden"
" among Deep Space markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1257
msgid "2.9 Doomsday Machines – Hidden GC"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1259
msgid ""
"• Features: The GC represents an ancient, super-advanced civilization. "
"You may not attack a GC but combat with the DM may occur in the GC hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1261
msgid ""
"• GC Discovery: The GC's location is not known at the start of the game. "
"The GC counter is seeded into an assortment of Deep Space markers "
"randomly placed near you.\n"
"The GC will randomly appear along the edge of your Home System markers. "
"Set aside the GC counter when assembling the random Deep Space counters "
"for a scenario. Also set aside 9 random Deep Space counters. The GC is "
"added face down, at random to the separated Deep Space counters. Place "
"these separate DS counters adjacent to your HS in hexes indicated by the "
"blue dots. The DM does not cause these DS markers to be flipped, see "
"[2.3.6]."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1264
msgid ""
"• GC Trade: You may trade with the GC by extending your MS Pipelines to "
"the GC hex as if it were one of your Colonies. Instead of gaining 1 CP "
"for this colony, you receive 5 CP per Econ Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1266
msgid ""
"• GC Loss Condition: If the GC is eliminated, you lose just as if your "
"own HW had been captured or eliminated."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1272
msgid "Space Amoebas (Solitaire Scenario 3)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1279
msgid ""
"Three types of Giant Space Amoebas surround your Home System. They spread"
" during each Economic Phase and must be researched by Science Vessels "
"before they can be attacked."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1281
msgid ""
"3.0 Space Amoebas\n"
"During the game, the Space Amoebas will multiply and attempt to destroy "
"the human player. There are similar rules for Space Amoebas included in "
"the Competitive Scenario Book ([CSB 10.0])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1284
msgid ""
"3.1 Setup\n"
"• There are 26 Home System markers for the player. The 30 CP Homeworld "
"should be placed in the hex with the \"H.\"\n"
"• Take ten of the 10 CP Deep Space Mineral markers and four of the Deep "
"Space Barren Planets and mix them up. Place them in the 14 Deep Space "
"hexes labeled \"DS.\" Do not use any other Deep Space markers. Leave the "
"other Deep Space hexes empty.\n"
"• There are three types of Giant Space Amoebas included in the game. One "
"is placed in each hex marked with an \"A.\""
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1289
msgid ""
"3.2 Special Rules\n"
"• The following rules are not used: Minesweepers, Non-Player Aliens, "
"Boarding Ships, Ground Combat, Titans, Facilities, and Ship Experience.\n"
"• The player pays no maintenance during this game.\n"
"• The Barren Planets do not have Non-Player Aliens on them.\n"
"• As in the multiplayer Space Amoeba scenarios, Minesweepers (SW) "
"represent Science Vessels (SV), which are needed to defeat the Amoebas. "
"Science (aka Minesweeper) technology must be researched to produce "
"Science Vessels. Use the costs for Minesweeper ships and Minesweeper "
"technology for producing Science Vessels.\n"
"• Researching Minesweepers (SW) instead gets the player Science Vessels "
"(SV) which are needed to defeat the Amoebas. Actual Minesweepers are not "
"used in this scenario.\n"
"• There are only two levels of Science technology. Ignore Minesweeper 3 "
"technology for this scenario."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1297
msgid ""
"3.2.1 Victory Conditions: The human player wins by destroying all Space "
"Amoebas."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1299
msgid ""
"3.3 Researching Space Amoebas\n"
"Science technology cannot be researched by the player until at least one "
"ship has been lost to any Amoeba. The player may move a \"brave\" ship "
"into an Amoeba's hex in order to find out what is coming toward their "
"empire. Note to self: Don't ever be a Scout pilot.\n"
"• Until the player has researched each Amoeba, on a type-by-type basis, "
"they cannot be attacked and will destroy all the player's ships (except "
"SVs) in the same hex. If SVs are present, they may research the Amoeba "
"before it destroys the other ships. If those SVs gather 10 or more "
"Research Points on that Amoeba type, the other ships will not be "
"automatically destroyed.\n"
"• Research Points carry over from turn to turn. A separate note should be"
" kept on each type of Space Amoeba.\n"
"• Each turn an SV is in the same hex with an Amoeba, one or more dice are"
" rolled for each SV to represent that ship's research into that type of "
"Amoeba.\n"
"  - 1-2: Two Research Points gained.\n"
"  - 3-5: One Research Point gained.\n"
"  - 6-8: Nothing.\n"
"  - 9-10: SV destroyed.\n"
"• Level 1 Science Vessels roll one die when researching.\n"
"• Level 2 Science Vessels get to roll two dice and take the best result.\n"
"• Level 2 Science technology can't be researched until a Level 1 SV has "
"made at least one research attempt on any one type of Amoeba.\n"
"• Each individual Amoeba does not need to be researched, but each TYPE "
"must be. Once the player has a total of 10 Research Points on a certain "
"TYPE of Amoeba, they may attack any Amoeba of that type for the rest of "
"the game.\n"
"• A Science Vessel may research an Amoeba on the same turn the ship moves"
" into its hex.\n"
"• Multiple SVs can research each turn they are in a hex with an Amoeba.\n"
"• If an SV shares a hex with an Amoeba type that has been completely "
"researched, that ship does not participate in the combat but must still "
"roll a die for research as normal and may be destroyed on a roll of 9-10."
" No further Research Points are gained.\n"
"• After 10 Research Points have been gathered on a type of Amoeba, those "
"Amoebas will no longer automatically destroy ships. Instead, combat "
"ensues as normal. However, Science Vessels never participate in combat "
"with an Amoeba."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1317
msgid ""
"3.4 Space Amoeba Characteristics\n"
"After 10 Research Points have been gathered on a type of Amoeba, the "
"Amoeba's characteristics are determined. Roll on the Amoeba "
"Characteristics Table and flip all Amoebas of that type to the "
"\"researched\" side. No two (or more) types of Amoebas will have the same"
" characteristics. Reroll any repeat result.\n"
"No retrofit (technology upgrade) is needed for ships in order to attack "
"([MRB 9.11.3])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1321
msgid ""
"3.5 Amoeba Characteristics Table\n"
"Roll 1: C7-1-1\n"
"Roll 2: D6-2-2\n"
"Roll 3: A7-2-2. This type of Amoeba is also vulnerable to fighters.\n"
"Roll 4: A7-2-2. This type of Amoeba becomes an A5-1-2 when faced by ONLY "
"Raiders.\n"
"Roll 5: B5-1-2. These Amoebas have voracious appetites and get two "
"attacks each round. Each of these attacks may lead to a Chain Attack "
"([3.6.3]).\n"
"Roll 6-7: A7-2-2. In any round in which there are 3 or more different "
"types of ships (for example: SC, DD, and CA) attacking these Amoebas, all"
" attacking ships get +1 to their attack.\n"
"Roll 8-10: These Amoebas can only be killed by detonating a ship inside "
"them, no adjustment to weapons will work on this type of Amoeba. Only one"
" ship may attempt this per turn. If the ship is a CA, BC, BB, or DN, the "
"Amoeba is destroyed. If the ship is a DD or MB the Amoeba is destroyed on"
" a roll of 1-8 and if the ship is a SC the Amoeba is destroyed on a roll "
"of 1-4. In all cases, the ship attempting this is destroyed. Only the "
"ships listed here can be used. If the Amoeba survives, other ships in the"
" hex with the Amoeba are destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1330
msgid ""
"3.6 Amoeba Properties\n"
"• All Amoebas have a Tactics level of 2.\n"
"• All Amoebas are immune to Cloaking and Fighters unless otherwise "
"specified.\n"
"• Ships never get a Fleet Size Bonus ([MRB 5.1.3]) against Amoebas."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1335
msgid ""
"3.6.1 Amoeba Target Priority: Each time an Amoeba attacks, these mindless"
" denizens of the interstellar void roll a die to determine which ship "
"they will attempt to swallow (attack). On a roll of 1-5 it will attack "
"the smallest ship in the combat. On a roll of 6-10 it will attack the "
"largest ship in the combat. Use the CP value of a ship to determine "
"largest and smallest. Since Flagships are irreplaceable, they are "
"considered to have the highest CP value. If there is a tie, the player "
"chooses the target of the Space Amoeba. If a player chooses to, they may "
"allow their SVs to be attacked."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1337
msgid ""
"3.6.2 Amoeba Attack Procedure: The Amoeba rolls one die and executes the "
"attack normally, comparing its Attack Strength to the ship's Defense "
"Strength (including technology). However, larger ships are even harder to"
" swallow. Ships with a Hull Size of 2 get an extra +1 to their Defense "
"Strength and ships with a Hull Size of 3 (or larger) get an extra +2 to "
"their Defense Strength. A successful attack results in the ship being "
"swallowed (destroyed) regardless of size. As always, a roll of a 1 is a "
"successful attack and will swallow a ship, regardless of size."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1339
msgid ""
"3.6.3 Chain Attacks: If an Amoeba successfully swallows a ship, and rolls"
" 2 or less than was needed, then the extra energy gained from swallowing "
"the ship allows the Amoeba to immediately attack again. This can happen "
"any number of times during a round of combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1341
msgid ""
"3.6.4 Amoeba Healing: After combat, damage to an Amoeba is healed in the "
"same way as ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1343
msgid ""
"3.7 Spreading of Space Amoebas\n"
"Amoebas never move. Once placed, an Amoeba counter never moves to a new "
"hex. Instead, Amoebas spread. At the start of an Economic Phase (before "
"the player makes any purchases), each Amoeba that is adjacent to a hex "
"without an Amoeba may spread. Place a new Amoeba of the same type in the "
"adjacent hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1346
msgid ""
"3.7.1 Spread Procedure: The following guidelines and restrictions apply "
"to the spreading:\n"
"• Space Amoebas begin to spread during the Economic Phase indicated on "
"the Difficulty Table ([3.9]).\n"
"• Only one Amoeba may ever be in a hex.\n"
"• Spreading is automatic; however, each Amoeba may only spread one time "
"into one hex during an Economic Phase.\n"
"• If more than one type of Amoeba is adjacent to an open hex, the human "
"player may decide which Amoeba spreads into the hex.\n"
"• If an Amoeba may spread into more than one hex, the player chooses "
"which hex it spreads into. However, the player must choose in such a way "
"to allow for maximum Amoeba spreading. If another open hex is available, "
"they cannot have an Amoeba spread into a hex that would stop a different "
"Amoeba from spreading.\n"
"• Unlike in multiplayer Amoeba scenarios, the spreading of Amoebas is not"
" affected by the presence or absence of planets.\n"
"• Newly placed Amoebas do not spread. New Amoebas placed that Economic "
"Phase should be marked in some way so that they are not accidentally "
"selected to spread.\n"
"• Because Amoebas are attracted to the energy signature of the player's "
"Empires, they will never spread outside of the map area denoted by the "
"chosen scenario map.\n"
"• Amoebas are not limited by the counter mix or quantity. If you run out "
"of one type, use a counter of another type and place a numeral marker on "
"it to show the true type of the Amoeba. Use substitutions when necessary."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1357
msgid ""
"3.7.2 Amoeba Contact with Ships: If there are ships in the hex in which "
"an Amoeba spreads, a special combat round occurs immediately during the "
"Economic Phase, with the Amoeba as the attacker. Of course, if that type "
"of Amoeba has not been fully researched yet, it automatically destroys "
"all ships that are not Science Vessels."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1359
msgid ""
"3.7.3 Amoeba Contact with System Markers: An Amoeba removes the System "
"marker (whether explored or not) in any hex in which it spreads (only "
"after defeating any ships present). If a hex has not been explored, the "
"Amoeba spreads normally and the System marker is removed, sight unseen.\n"
"If a Black Hole has been revealed, an Amoeba will not spread into that "
"hex. In all other cases, Amoebas are unaffected by System markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1362
msgid ""
"3.8 Space Amoebas and Mines\n"
"Space Amoebas are hindered from spreading by Mines. However, Mines never "
"affect Amoebas like they do ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1365
msgid ""
"3.8.1 Procedure: If the player moves only a Mine (or a Mine and a Science"
" Vessel) into the same hex as an Amoeba, no combat occurs. In the "
"Economic Phase, the Mine is removed, and that Amoeba does not spread "
"during that one Economic Phase. No other harm comes to the Amoeba."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1367
msgid ""
"3.8.2 Contact with Mines: Amoebas may spread onto Mines normally; in "
"which case the Mines have no effect and are removed from the map. A Mine "
"only stops an Amoeba from spreading if it is in the same hex as the "
"Amoeba at the start of the Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1369
msgid ""
"3.8.3 Adapting to Mines: See [CSB 10.8.3]. However, when an Amoeba adapts"
" to Mines, it only affects Amoebas of that type."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1371
msgid ""
"3.8.4 One Roll per Economic Phase: The roll to see if the Amoebas adapt "
"to Mines is made only once per Amoeba type per Economic Phase, regardless"
" of how many Amoebas were prevented from spreading."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1373
msgid ""
"3.9 Difficulty Table\n"
"Space Amoebas do NOT spread in the first Economic Phase. The difficulty "
"level of the game is determined by the Economic Phase in which the "
"Amoebas start to spread.\n"
"Easy: Amoebas start spreading in Economic Phase 7\n"
"Normal: Amoebas start spreading in Economic Phase 6\n"
"Hard: Amoebas start spreading in Economic Phase 5\n"
"Harder: Amoebas start spreading in Economic Phase 4\n"
"Good Luck!: Amoebas start spreading in Economic Phase 4* (*Both the "
"Attack and Defense Strengths of all Amoebas are increased by 1.)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1382
msgid "3 A7-2-2. This type of Amoeba is also vulnerable to fighters."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1383
msgid ""
"5 B5-1-2. These Amoebas have voracious appetites and get two attacks each"
" round. Each of these attacks may lead to a Chain Attack ([3.6.3])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1384
msgid ""
"8-10 These Amoebas can only be killed by detonating a ship inside them, "
"no adjustment to weapons will work on this type of Amoeba. Only one ship "
"may attempt this per turn. If the ship is a CA, BC, BB, or DN, the Amoeba"
" is destroyed. If the ship is a DD or MB the Amoeba is destroyed on a "
"roll of 1-8 and if the ship is a SC the Amoeba is destroyed on a roll of "
"1-4. In all cases, the ship attempting this is destroyed. Only the ships "
"listed here can be used. If the Amoeba survives, other ships in the hex "
"with the Amoeba are destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1388
msgid ""
"Design Note: In sci-fi terms, the Amoeba can be killed if the player "
"slightly tweaks their weapons – by adjusting the frequency to the upper "
"EM band, by adjusting the phase, by reversing the polarity, or by doing "
"something else pseudo-scientific sounding. The specific adjustment is not"
" important. It means it is now possible to (immediately) attack them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1394
msgid "Solitaire Alien Empire — Non-Victory Point Rules (Scenarios 4 & 5)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1402
msgid ""
"One player vs 2 or 3 Alien Players. Two map layouts available (Map 1 and "
"Map 2). APs use automated Economic Rolls to generate fleets. Only Basic "
"Unit types."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1404
msgid "4.0 Solitaire Alien Empire - Non-Victory Point Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1406
msgid ""
"4.0.1 Victory Conditions: One player sets up and plays their empire as "
"normal. Two or three Alien Players (APs) are trying to destroy the human "
"player. The player wins by destroying the Homeworlds of all APs. The game"
" can continue beyond Econ Phase 20. If it does, alternate the rolls on "
"the AP Economic Sheet between rows 19 and 20."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1408
msgid ""
"4.0.2 Special Rules: The human player may not use Decoys. There is no "
"need for a turn order bid - the human player always takes their turn "
"before the APs and the APs always resolve their Economic Phases after the"
" player. Barren Planets found in Deep Space are not inhabited by Non-"
"Player Aliens (NPAs; [MRB 18.0]). In general, where the solitaire rules "
"are silent, use common sense and play the APs intelligently."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1410
msgid ""
"Only Basic Units Types are used ([MRB 8.0]).\n"
"Fast Technology is not used ([MRB 9.9]).\n"
"Empire Advantages are not used ([MRB 10.0]).\n"
"Alien Technology cards are not used ([MRB 11.0]).\n"
"Crew Cards are not used ([MRB 12.0]).\n"
"Defense Satellite Networks are not used ([MRB 14.0]).\n"
"Additional Terrain ([MRB 25.0]) may be used.\n"
"Doomsday Machines ([MRB 29.0]) may be used.\n"
"Instant Technology Upgrades ([MRB 30.0]) may be used.\n"
"Black Hole Slingshots ([MRB 31.0]) may be used.\n"
"All other rules after [MRB 18.0] are not used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1422
msgid ""
"4.1 Alien Player Homeworlds\n"
"• APs each have a Homeworld. Use the Homeworlds and ships from the unused"
" player colors. An AP Homeworld represents the entire empire and "
"resources of that AP.\n"
"• Each AP starts with one Base on their Homeworld.\n"
"• APs never use MS Pipelines, Colony Ships, Shipyards, Mining Ships, or "
"Decoys.\n"
"• An AP is eliminated when its Homeworld is eliminated. At that point it "
"will no longer produce ships, but existing ships will continue to fight "
"to the death.\n"
"• Until an AP launches a fleet ([4.3]), the only actions that need to be "
"taken for them (other than defending against an attack) occur in the "
"Economic Phase.\n"
"• In combat, the AP never screens ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1430
msgid ""
"4.2 AP Economic Rolls\n"
"During the Economic Phase, after the player completes their actions, each"
" AP takes the following actions:\n"
"• APs make their Economic Roll(s). Each AP starts with one Economic Roll "
"(Econ Roll). If the result is Economy, an Extra Economic Roll is gained "
"every Economic Phase starting three Economic Phases later.\n"
"• If any other result is rolled, a number of CP (5, 10, or 15) is added "
"in the appropriate column depending on difficulty. CP put in the Defense "
"column are doubled. These columns (Fleet, Technology, Defense) carry over"
" from turn to turn. The Defense column maxes out at 50 CP, excess is "
"placed into Fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1435
msgid ""
"Difficulty Table:\n"
"Easy: 2 APs, 5 CP per roll\n"
"Normal: 3 APs, 5 CP per roll\n"
"Hard: 2 APs, 10 CP per roll\n"
"Harder: 3 APs, 10 CP per roll\n"
"Really Tough: 2 APs, 15 CP per roll\n"
"Good Luck!: 3 APs, 15 CP per roll"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1443
msgid ""
"4.3 AP Fleet Launch Rolls\n"
"When all Economic Rolls have been made, the Fleet Launch roll is made. A "
"fleet will never launch if there is less than 6 CP in the Fleet column or"
" if there are already 3 fleets in play for this AP.\n"
"• If AP has Fighter Tech with 27+ CP in Fleet and human has not shown "
"equivalent PD Tech, apply -2 modifier to Fleet Launch roll.\n"
"• If AP has Cloaking Tech with 12+ CP in Fleet and human has not shown "
"equivalent Scanner Tech, apply -2 modifier (cumulative).\n"
"• If Fleet Launch is made, determine if it is a Raider fleet ([4.4]). "
"Raider fleets are built immediately. Non-Raider fleets are not built "
"until first combat.\n"
"• All new fleets are placed on this AP's Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1450
msgid ""
"4.4 AP Raider Fleets\n"
"A fleet is a Raider fleet if: AP has Cloaking technology, has at least 12"
" CP in Fleet column, and human has not shown equivalent Scanner "
"technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1453
msgid ""
"4.5 AP Technology Purchasing\n"
"• APs start with Mine technology ([MRB 17.1]).\n"
"• AP does not attempt to purchase tech if less than 20 CP in Tech Column."
"\n"
"• Whenever a fleet is launched, roll for Movement tech. On 1-4, purchase "
"next level if affordable.\n"
"• Technologies other than Movement are not purchased until combat occurs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1459
msgid ""
"4.5.1 Order of Purchases: Once in combat, spend all tech CP in this "
"order:\n"
"• Raider fleet with Cloaking 1: roll 1-6 buy Cloaking 2, 7-10 proceed to "
"chart.\n"
"• If human used Fighters and AP has no PD, purchase PD 1.\n"
"• If human showed Mines and AP has no Minesweeper, purchase Minesweeper "
"1.\n"
"• If human used Raiders and AP has no adequate Scanner: roll 1-4 purchase"
" Scanner, 5-10 skip.\n"
"• Ship Size: roll on table (SS1: Auto, SS2: 1-7, SS3: 1-6, SS4: 1-5, SS5:"
" 1-3).\n"
"• If AP has Fighter tech and human has not shown PD: roll 1-6 buy next "
"Fighter level.\n"
"• Remaining CP: roll on Technology Purchase Table (1-2 Attack, 3-4 "
"Defense, 5 Tactics*, 6 Cloak**, 7 Scan, 8 Fighter, 9 PD, 10 Minesweeper)."
"\n"
"*If Tactics rolled and AP not at Attack 2 or Defense 2, purchase lower of"
" Attack/Defense instead.\n"
"**If human has shown Scanner 2, reroll 6s."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1470
msgid ""
"4.6 AP Fleet Building\n"
"After tech spent, fleet CP used to purchase ships:\n"
"• Raider fleet: all points on Raiders.\n"
"• If AP has Fighter tech and human has not shown PD: create Carrier fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1475
msgid ""
"4.6.1 Building Priorities (non-Raider):\n"
"• LARGEST SHIP FIRST.\n"
"• POSSIBLE DESTROYER if AP has Scanner tech matching human Cloaking.\n"
"• REMAINING SHIPS: roll Fleet Composition (3 or less: Largest Fleet, 4-6:"
" Balanced, 7-10: Largest Ships). -2 modifier if human has used Fighters "
"and AP has PD."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1480
msgid ""
"4.6.2 Fleet Composition explained:\n"
"• LARGEST FLEET: maximize ship count.\n"
"• LARGEST SHIPS: maximize ship size.\n"
"• BALANCED: maximize ships using highest Attack/Defense tech."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1485
msgid ""
"4.6.3 No Minesweepers: AP Scouts automatically equipped with Minesweeper "
"tech. AP never purchases Minesweeper ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1487
msgid "4.7 AP Fleet Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1489
msgid ""
"4.7.1 Non-Raider Fleet Movement: Move toward Colony reachable in fewest "
"Economic Phases. Prefer undefended Colonies (SY + single SC not "
"considered defended). AP fleets never retreat. Cannot enter Supernovas, "
"Cosmic Storms, or Black Holes. Stop in terrain that benefits them most. "
"If hex has unexplored marker, do not flip it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1491
msgid ""
"4.7.2 Raider Fleet Movement: Same as normal but avoid combat with larger "
"player fleets (in CP). Never attack Colony guarded by larger force. "
"Redirect if guard becomes equal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1493
msgid ""
"4.8 AP Homeworld Defense\n"
"Defense CP not used until Homeworld attacked. AP spends all Fleet, Tech, "
"and Defense CP to build fleets, Bases, and Mines. No Movement tech roll. "
"Reroll 10s on Technology Purchase Table.\n"
"Defense Composition: Roll 1-3 Mines, 4-7 Balanced, 8-10 Most Bases."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1497
msgid ""
"4.9 Alien Player Map 1 (Solitaire Scenario 4)\n"
"26 Home System markers. Homeworld on \"H.\" APs on \"2s\" (2 APs) or "
"\"2s\" and \"3\" (3 APs). Player uses 20 CP Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1500
msgid ""
"4.10 Alien Player Map 2 (Solitaire Scenario 5)\n"
"25 Home System markers (Black Hole removed). Homeworld on \"X.\" DS "
"markers within 7 hexes. APs on \"2s\" and \"3.\" Player uses 20 CP "
"Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1507
msgid "Using Close Encounters Rules in Solitaire Alien Empire"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1514
msgid ""
"Optional overlay for Solitaire Scenarios 4 or 5 adding Close Encounters "
"rules."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1516
msgid ""
"5.0 Using Close Encounters Rules in Solitaire Alien Empire Scenarios - "
"Non-Victory Point Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1518
msgid ""
"It is possible to play Solitaire Scenarios (4.9 or 4.10) with some of the"
" new rules and technologies from Close Encounters. This is accomplished "
"using the AP Flowcharts in the last pages of this scenario book and "
"allows for the use of the following additions:\n"
"• Alien Technology cards ([MRB 11.0])\n"
"• Crew cards ([MRB 12.0])\n"
"• Ship Experience ([MRB 37.0])\n"
"• Boarding Ships ([MRB 19.0])\n"
"• Security Forces ([MRB 20.0])\n"
"• Ground Combat ([MRB 21.0])\n"
"• Titans ([MRB 22.0])\n"
"• Resource cards ([MRB 39.0])"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1528
msgid ""
"5.1 Setup\n"
"Choose either Solitaire Scenario and set up the map as originally "
"indicated. Use the 30 CP Homeworld instead."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1531
msgid ""
"5.2 Special Rules\n"
"• Victory Conditions remain the same as originally indicated.\n"
"• The AP does not use the Alien Player Victory Point Track; this mechanic"
" is introduced in section [6.3.3].\n"
"• The AP only builds either regular fleets or Raider fleets as in the "
"original game.\n"
"• Like the human player, the AP may now use the features listed above "
"except Alien Technology cards, which they cannot acquire.\n"
"• Use the original \"Alien Economic Sheet\" on page 56.\n"
"• A Colony captured by the AP cannot be bombarded by the human player. "
"The AP will defend captured Colonies with Mines, Bases, and Ground Units."
"\n"
"• APs may gain technology by capturing a player Colony ([MRB 21.13.5]; "
"[MRB 21.13.6]). Human player may steal technology from AP by capturing AP"
" Homeworld with Ground Units.\n"
"• Facilities ([MRB 36.0]) are not used.\n"
"• Empire Advantages ([MRB 10.0]) may not be used.\n"
"• A Flagship ([MRB 23.0]) may be used by the human player only.\n"
"• If human player colonizes a Deep Space Barren Planet, they may gain an "
"Alien Technology card as per [MRB 11.1]."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1544
msgid ""
"5.3 Alien Player Behavior\n"
"Follow the AP flowcharts starting on page 57, with exceptions:\n"
"• Econ Roll may result in Extra Econ as per original \"Alien Economic "
"Sheet\" ([4.2]).\n"
"• AP does not colonize Barren Planets.\n"
"• AP does not have a Bank ([6.5.2]).\n"
"• AP does not launch Expansion or Extermination fleets. Non-Raider fleets"
" treated as regular fleets.\n"
"• Regular AP fleets always target the nearest, least defended Colony.\n"
"• During ship purchasing, follow the branch for Carriers, Raiders, "
"Expansion fleets and Ground Combat units. Ignore Extermination branch. "
"All Regular AP fleets get a fully loaded Transport for free.\n"
"• Ignore items specific to Victory Point scenarios ([6.0]) including "
"Bank, AP movement, exploration and colonizing rules."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1558
msgid "Solitaire Alien Empire — Victory Point Rules (Scenario 6)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1565
msgid ""
"Advanced solitaire scenario with Galactic Capitol, Warp Points, Victory "
"Points tracking, and Black Hole Jumping technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1567
msgid "6.0 Solitaire Alien Empire - Victory Point Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1569
msgid ""
"Evil alien races are trying to eXplore, eXpand, eXploit, and eXterminate "
"your end of the galaxy and must be stopped!"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1571
msgid ""
"Note: This scenario assumes a good understanding of the solitaire rules "
"in section [4.0]."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1573
msgid "6.1 Setup"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1575
msgid ""
"6.1.1 Homeworlds: 30 CP Homeworld on the \"X.\" \"AP\" marks the two "
"Alien Player Homeworlds."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1577
msgid "6.1.2 Starting Tech: Player starts with Terraforming 1 and Exploration 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1579
msgid ""
"6.1.3 Galactic Capitol: Ancient GC in the center surrounded by six "
"Nebulae. Place a 5 CP Colony marker on it. Generates militia if attacked "
"by AP Ground Units. Grows back up to 5 CP during Economic Phase. Player "
"cannot bombard, capture, or deliver Minerals to it, but may place Ground "
"Units to defend."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1581
msgid "6.1.4 Galactic Minerals: 10-Mineral counter at GC. Respawns when consumed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1583
msgid ""
"6.1.5 Warp Points: WP at GC (no counter) plus WP on each side of player's"
" Home System. All connected to GC."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1585
msgid ""
"6.1.6 Deep Space Markers: Placed everywhere above the black line except "
"around GC, player's HS, and WP spaces."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1587
msgid "6.1.7 Alien Planets: 30 CP Homeworld markers on \"AP\" spaces."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1589
msgid "6.1.8 Starting CP: Each AP starts with 100 CP in Expansion/Defense Bank."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1591
msgid ""
"6.2 AP Difficulty - VP Rules:\n"
"Easy: 5 CP/Econ Roll, Bank 100, Max Defense 50\n"
"Normal: 10 CP/Econ Roll, Bank 100, Max Defense 50\n"
"Hard: 15 CP/Econ Roll, Bank 100, Max Defense 50"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1596
msgid "6.3 Victory Conditions"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1598
msgid ""
"6.3.1 Alien Victory: Destroy GC, destroy player's Homeworld, or "
"accumulate 10 VPs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1600
msgid "6.3.2 Human Victory: Destroy both AP Homeworlds."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1602
msgid ""
"6.3.3 Tracking VPs: Shared VP total. Always 10 for AP victory.\n"
"AP colonizes/captures DS planet: +2 VPs\n"
"AP destroys/captures player Colony: +2 VPs\n"
"Player destroys/(re)captures AP Colony: -2 VPs\n"
"Alien Technology cards in AP possession: +1 VP each"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1608
msgid "6.3.4 Game Length: Can continue beyond Econ Phase 20."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1610
msgid ""
"6.4 Special Rules\n"
"Ship Experience ([MRB 37.0]), NPAs ([MRB 18.0]), Transports/Ground Combat"
" ([MRB 21.0]) used. Human may use Replicators expansion technologies."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1613
msgid ""
"6.4.1 Prohibited: Empire Advantages, Crew cards, Facilities, Resource "
"cards. APs don't use Replicators technologies."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1615
msgid ""
"6.4.2 Black Hole Jumping: 2 levels (20 CP / 40 CP). Level 1: enter Black "
"Holes without survival roll. Level 2: treat all face-up Black Holes and "
"Warp Points as connected. Hard difficulty requires Movement 3 first."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1617
msgid "6.4.3 Alien Starting Tech: Terraforming 1, Exploration 1, Ground Combat 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1619
msgid "6.4.4 Alien Colonies: APs can capture or build Colonies."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1621
msgid ""
"6.4.5 Attacking Alien Colonies: Player may attack/capture AP Colonies. "
"Destroyed/captured = -2 VPs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1623
msgid ""
"6.4.6 APs Gaining Alien Tech Cards: If AP captures NPA planet, draw Alien"
" Tech card. Cannot use effects but each card = +1 VP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1625
msgid ""
"6.4.7 Stealing Alien Tech Cards: Human can steal (random) from AP by "
"capturing AP Colony in DS with Ground Units."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1627
msgid ""
"6.4.8 Capturing AP Technology: Player gains tech by capturing AP Colonies"
" ([MRB 21.13.6]). Treated as DS Colonies."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1629
msgid ""
"6.4.9 Eliminating AP Homeworlds: Eliminated AP continues acting. Units "
"not removed. Cannot gain VP/cards but can still cause loss."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1631
msgid "6.5 Alien Player Behavior"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1633
msgid ""
"6.5.1 Fleet Types: Extermination ([6.6]), Expansion ([6.7]), or Raider "
"([6.9]). Max 3 fleets per AP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1635
msgid ""
"6.5.2 Bank and Defense Limits: Expansion fleet adds 50 CP from Bank. "
"Defense maxes at 50 CP. Reroll Defense results at max."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1637
msgid "6.5.3 Economic Phase: After player."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1639
msgid "6.5.4 Shared Intelligence: APs share all info."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1641
msgid ""
"6.5.5 Resource Gathering: Extermination/Expansion fleets collect Minerals"
" for 1 extra Econ Roll next phase. Raiders cannot."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1643
msgid "6.5.6 Space Wrecks: Destroyed immediately. No VPs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1645
msgid ""
"6.5.7 Colonization: AP may invade or build Colony Ship ([6.8.4]). Each "
"producing AP Colony gives 1 extra Econ Roll."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1647
msgid ""
"6.5.8 Blockaded AP Homeworlds: Continue Economic Phases but no fleet "
"launch. All CP to Defense/Bank. Next Movement Phase launches Defense "
"fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1649
msgid "6.5.9 Combat: Never retreats. Positions defensively if out of range."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1651
msgid "6.5.10 Screening: As a human player would."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1653
msgid "6.5.11 Captured Ships: Cannot be scrapped for tech."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1655
msgid ""
"6.5.12 Capturing Player Tech: Gains tech as in competitive game ([MRB "
"21.13]). Also gains 10 CP in Tech column."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1657
msgid "6.5.13 Experience: Tracked normally ([MRB 37.0])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1659
msgid ""
"6.5.14 Minesweepers: AP Scouts equip Minesweeper tech. No Minesweeper "
"ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1661
msgid "6.5.15 Regional Map/Space Pirates: No effect on AP. Discard."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1663
msgid "6.5.16 AP avoids Cosmic Storms if possible. Moves through Folds normally."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1665
msgid ""
"6.6 Extermination Fleets\n"
"6.6.1 Targeting: Random - player's Homeworld or GC.\n"
"6.6.2 Movement: Beeline to destination, avoiding combat and other "
"Colonies if able."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1669
msgid ""
"6.7 Expansion Fleets\n"
"6.7.1 Targeting: Closest NPA planet or player Colony. If equidistant, "
"choose one enabling more DS exploration.\n"
"6.7.2 Movement: Toward target, avoiding Homeworlds and GC. Destinations "
"reset each Movement Phase. Remainder stays and defends permanently "
"(doesn't count for 3 fleet limit)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1673
msgid ""
"6.8 Non-Raider Fleet Movement and Exploration\n"
"6.8.1 Movement: Hindered by terrain like human fleets.\n"
"6.8.2 Exploration: Equivalent of one Cruiser with Exploration 1. One DS "
"marker per fleet per turn.\n"
"6.8.3 Barren Planets: Place 4 random NPA counters. Combat occurs.\n"
"6.8.4 Colonizing: If AP won space combat, Colony Ship + 2d10 CP escorts "
"placed at nearest AP Colony/Homeworld at no cost."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1679
msgid ""
"6.9 Raider Fleets\n"
"As in the base game, the AP may launch a Raider fleet instead of a normal"
" fleet. These fleets always target the nearest, least defended player "
"Colony. If 3 fleets already in play for this AP, launch is cancelled."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1682
msgid ""
"6.9.1 Non-Player Aliens: Raider fleets will remain cloaked when in the "
"same hex as an NPA planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1684
msgid ""
"6.9.2 May Not Capture Colonies: Unlike Expansion and Extermination "
"fleets, Raider fleets have no chance of building Ground Units to capture "
"a Colony. They may still destroy a Colony and trigger the construction of"
" a Colony Ship ([6.8.4])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1686
msgid ""
"6.9.3 Deep Space Markers: Unlike Expansion and Extermination fleets, "
"Raider fleets are unaffected by unrevealed Deep Space markers and do not "
"cause them to become flipped. A player may not enter a hex with an "
"unrevealed Deep Space marker that is occupied by a Raider fleet. A player"
" may not use Exploration technology on an unrevealed Deep Space marker in"
" the same hex as a Raider fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1688
msgid ""
"6.9.4 Asteroids and Nebulae: Raider fleets are affected by these terrain "
"types just like human fleets. They will avoid Nebulae if able as long as "
"doing so does not change the number of Economic Phases it takes to reach "
"their destination."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1690
msgid ""
"6.9.5 Avoiding Combat: Raiders will avoid combat with player fleets if "
"the player fleet has greater CP than the Raider fleet. They also avoid "
"combat with a fleet containing a Flagship if the rest of the Flagship's "
"fleet CP cost is greater than half the Raider fleet's CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1693
msgid "AP destroys or captures a player Colony +2 VPs"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1694
msgid "Alien Technology cards in AP’s possession +1 VP each"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1700
msgid "Replicator Solitaire (Scenarios 7 & 8)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1708
msgid ""
"Solitaire scenario against the Replicators. Two map sizes: Standard "
"([7.13]) and Large ([7.14]). Extensive autonomous Replicator AI rules for"
" exploration, fleet formation, movement, combat, and production."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1710
msgid ""
"7.0 Replicator Solitaire\n"
"This solitaire scenario against the Replicators includes several "
"flowcharts for reference on pages 62-67."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1713
msgid ""
"7.1 Map Setup\n"
"• Use either the Normal ([7.13]) or Large ([7.14]) Replicator Solitaire "
"map.\n"
"• Place each Homeworld anywhere in the Home System row furthest from the "
"opponent."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1717
msgid "7.2 Starting Forces & Technology"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1719
msgid ""
"7.2.1 Human Player: 30 CP Homeworld, 4 Colony Ships, 4 Shipyards, 3 "
"Scouts, 1 Miner, 1 Flagship (optional)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1721
msgid ""
"7.2.2 Replicators: Full Homeworld, 6 Type 0 ships, 1 Flagship (optional),"
" Point Defense, Scanners, Minesweepers, Move 2 (Move 3 with <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Fast Replicators [g][#60][/g]</span> advantage)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1723
msgid "7.3 Special Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1725
msgid ""
"7.3.1 Difficulty Level:\n"
"Easy: Player starts with two additional Colony Ships.\n"
"Normal: No changes.\n"
"Hard: Replicators start with two additional Hull Points and one free RP.\n"
"Impossible: Replicators start with three additional Hull Points and two "
"free RPs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1731
msgid ""
"7.3.2 Hulls: \"Hull Size\" and \"Hull Points\" are equivalent when "
"comparing."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1733
msgid ""
"7.3.3 Excluded Rules (*never used in any Replicators scenario):\n"
"*Facilities, *Terraforming 2, *Unique Ships, *Experience, *Reaction "
"Movement, *Space Amoebas, *Blood Brothers, Decoys, Resource Cards, "
"*Galactic Capitol, Regional Maps, Space Pirates, Warp Points, Doomsday "
"Machines."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1736
msgid ""
"7.3.4 NPAs and Alien Tech: Barren Planets have NPAs ([MRB 18.0]). Remove "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Minesweep Jammer [g][#24][/g]</span> from "
"Alien Tech deck."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1738
msgid ""
"7.3.5 Empire Advantages: Remove <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Warp Gates"
" [g][#63][/g]</span> Replicator EA. Deal 2 EA + 1 Replicator EA. After "
"player selects, reveal Replicator EA."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1740
msgid ""
"7.3.6 Initiative: Replicators always have Initiative unless human spends "
"15 CP. Replicators never spend CP on Initiative."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1742
msgid ""
"7.3.7 Replicator Ship Behavior: Facedown = Hulls. Flagship and "
"Exploration ships always faceup. Ships entering Replicator Colony convert"
" back to Hulls."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1744
msgid "7.3.8 Miscellaneous: No hidden information. Roll die for unclear choices."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1746
msgid ""
"7.4 Exploration Procedures\n"
"After Replicator HS fully explored, Replicators receive Exploration tech "
"(free) and 3 Exploration ships placed at the 3 Full Colonies closest to "
"unexplored DS hexes. No Replicator ship ever enters unexplored DS hex. "
"Exploration ships use Exploration tech only."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1749
msgid ""
"7.4.1 Flagship Exploration: Replicator Flagship does not equip "
"Exploration tech."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1751
msgid ""
"7.5 Exploration Ships\n"
"One explores toward human player HS, two explore DS near Replicator HS."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1754
msgid ""
"7.5.1 Exploring Toward Human Player: Creates direct explored path.\n"
"7.5.2 Exploring Nearby DS: Row by row from Replicator HS.\n"
"7.5.3 Priorities: Closest unexplored DS marker. Ties broken by proximity "
"to explored hexes, then distance from Replicator HS.\n"
"7.5.4 Additional Rules: Never join Fleets. Never enter hex with human "
"ships. Always retreat. If all eliminated, create replacement. After DS "
"fully explored, convert to 2 Hulls."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1759
msgid ""
"7.6 Replicator Movement\n"
"Never enter Black Holes or Supernovas. Prefer converting to Hulls via "
"Replicator Colony. Prioritize hexes with unescorted non-combat ships and "
"Asteroids/Nebulae."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1762
msgid ""
"7.6.1 During HS Exploration: Move into nearest unexplored HS hex. "
"Minerals absorbed, planets colonized immediately.\n"
"7.6.2 HS Fully Explored: All ships (except Exploration) form/join Fleets."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1765
msgid ""
"7.7 Fleet Formation\n"
"Fleets represented by Fleet markers. Multiple ships in a hex does NOT "
"make a Fleet. Fleets never split (except Tasks). Only combine to attack "
"on same turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1768
msgid ""
"7.7.1 Forming Fleets: Ships move toward nearest Fleet and join.\n"
"7.7.2 The First Fleet: Forms when HS fully explored. Follows the human-"
"bound Exploration ship.\n"
"7.7.3 Additional Fleets: Form when: (a) separate explored path to human "
"HS exists (not within 4 hexes of another Fleet), or (b) human ship closer"
" to Replicator Colony than any Fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1772
msgid ""
"7.8 Fleet Movement\n"
"Steps: 1. Move Exploration ships. 2. Form additional Fleets. 3. Move "
"Fleets. 4. Move non-Fleet ships toward Fleets."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1775
msgid ""
"7.8.1 Movement Priorities:\n"
"1. Attack a Colony (undefended or Equal/Inferior guard).\n"
"2. Attack an Inferior Fleet (limited by Self-Preservation).\n"
"3. Attack an Equal Fleet if it could attack Replicator Colony.\n"
"4. Attack NPA planet with 12+ Hull Points (limited by Self-Preservation)."
"\n"
"5. Move toward/away from human Colony or ships via explored path (limited"
" by Self-Preservation)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1782
msgid ""
"7.8.2 Fleet Comparison: Total Hull Points each side. Ignore non-"
"combat/Exploration ships. Human Base = double (6 HP). Mine = 1.5 HP. 25%+"
" more = Superior, other = Inferior. Otherwise Equal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1784
msgid ""
"7.8.3 Self-Preservation: Priorities 2, 4, 5 limited. Replicators won't "
"move where a Superior fleet could attack them. Never fall back beyond "
"Homeworld. Replicators ignore Black Hole Slingshot possibility when "
"applying Self-Preservation."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1786
msgid ""
"7.8.4 Replicator Fleet Movement Examples: Human player has two Destroyers"
" (2 HP) in one hex and three Destroyers (3 HP) in an adjacent hex. "
"Replicators have a Fleet of three Hulls two hexes away from both. No "
"Colony can be attacked (Priority 1)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1788
msgid ""
"• If Fleet can move 2 hexes: attacks the 2-DD fleet (Priority 2). Won't "
"attack the 3-DD fleet (not Inferior). Post-battle losses becoming "
"Inferior to the 3-DD fleet is not considered."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1790
msgid ""
"• If Fleet can move 2 hexes AND one more Hull can also reach: Hull "
"combines with Fleet, both human fleets now Inferior, so Replicators "
"attack the 3-DD fleet (strongest Inferior, Priority 2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1792
msgid ""
"• If Fleet can only move 1 hex: won't move into any hex where both human "
"fleets could attack together. 5 DDs Superior to 3 Hulls. Priority 5 "
"limited by Self-Preservation."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1794
msgid ""
"• If Replicators move 1 hex but human moves 2: Fleet retreats to a hex at"
" least 3 hexes from one human fleet (Self-Preservation). May retreat "
"toward Replicator HS. If Asteroid hex is adjacent and human can't enter "
"it, Fleet enters it to stay close without being attacked."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1796
msgid ""
"• If both move 1 hex near human HS: Fleet moves to hex closest to a human"
" Colony (Priority 5) where it can't be attacked by both human fleets "
"together."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1798
msgid ""
"7.9 Replicator Tasks\n"
"7.9.1 Gain NPA RP: Assign nearest ship to attack NPA planet.\n"
"7.9.2 Gain Human RP: If attack would earn RP, assign one ship.\n"
"7.9.3 Colonize Undefended Planet: Assign ship to colonize.\n"
"7.9.4 Conquer NPA Planet: Only on Large map, before Econ Phase 10, with "
"10+ ships near HS."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1804
msgid "7.10 Colonization: Always expend one Hull Point only."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1806
msgid "7.11 Combat"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1808
msgid ""
"7.11.1 Converting Hulls to Ships: Follow steps in order:\n"
"7.11.1.1 Unescorted Non-Combat: Destroyed immediately.\n"
"7.11.1.2 Lone SC/DD/Transport: Roll 1-5 combat, 6-10 eliminate without "
"conversion.\n"
"7.11.1.3 Scan Ships: Based on Raider presence (die roll tables).\n"
"7.11.1.4 Minesweepers: Based on Mine presence (die roll tables).\n"
"7.11.1.5 Point Defense: Based on Fighter presence (die roll tables).\n"
"7.11.1.6 Remaining: Convert to highest RP ships possible."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1816
msgid ""
"7.11.1.7 Conversion Example: The Replicators have 5 RP and are attacking."
" They have one SW, one PD, two Type II ships, and 10 unrevealed Hulls. "
"The human player has seven Mines, three Fighters, one CV, and two DDs. "
"There is a Raider within three hexes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1818
msgid ""
"Steps 7.11.1.1 & 7.11.1.2 are skipped (no unescorted non-combat, no lone "
"SD/DD/Transport)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1820
msgid ""
"7.11.1.3: Raiders encountered before + Raider within 3 hexes = third row."
" Roll 9 = two Hulls convert to Scan ships. 8 unrevealed Hulls remain."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1822
msgid ""
"7.11.1.4: Mines in battle + encountered before = last row. Roll 2 = "
"enough SW to clear half Mines. They have Minesweeping 2 (swept 3 Mines "
"before). One SW already present, convert one Hull to add another SW = "
"clear 4 Mines. 7 unrevealed Hulls remain."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1824
msgid ""
"7.11.1.5: Fighters in battle + encountered before = fifth row. Roll 1 = "
"one PD hull, but PD already present, so no additional PD."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1826
msgid ""
"7.11.1.6: 7 remaining Hulls convert to three Type V ships and one Type IV"
" ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1828
msgid ""
"Resulting Fleet: one Scan, two SWs, one PD, two Type II, one Type IV, "
"three Type V."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1830
msgid ""
"7.11.2 Attack Priorities: PD fires at Fighters. Scan fires at Raiders. "
"Others: smallest Hull, lowest Defense, highest Attack, unfired."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1832
msgid ""
"7.11.3 Screening: Replicators never screen. Scan/SW ships only targetable"
" if human has more ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1834
msgid ""
"7.11.4 Retreat: If human has 3x Hull Points. Flagship retreats at 2 "
"damage."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1836
msgid ""
"7.12 Economic Phase\n"
"Each Full Colony produces one Hull. Can carry over 30+ CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1839
msgid ""
"7.12.1 Production: Econ 1-3: Buy extra Hull at HW for 8 CP.\n"
"Econ 4+: Based on Empire Advantage or die roll (1-4: Hull 8 CP, 5-8: RP "
"30 CP, 9-10: Move tech 20 CP)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1842
msgid "7.13 Replicators Standard: Standard-size map."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1844
msgid "7.14 Replicators Large: Larger map with more Deep Space rows."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1847
msgid ""
"Raiders in the battle or within 3 hexes of the battle? No 1-10 Raiders in"
" the battle or within 3 hexes of the battle? Yes Replicators encountered "
"previously? No 1-8 9-10 Raiders in the battle or within 3 hexes of the "
"battle? Yes Replicators encountered previously? Yes 1 2-9 10"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1850
msgid ""
"PLAY NOTE: The Replicator AI does not have Exploration technology or "
"Exploration ships until after the Home System is completely explored "
"([7.4])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1853
msgid ""
"Designer Note: Similar to your fleets, each Replicator Fleet has a "
"purpose – whether to attack/defend or hunt down a ship in their space. "
"That purpose may change over time, but Fleet creation should be "
"considered with that purpose in mind."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1854
msgid ""
"Designer Note: Making special rules for them to use single hull ships in "
"the vicinity or when to just colonize with a larger ship was not worth "
"the effort. This is much simpler."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1860
msgid "Doomsday Machine Coop (2-Player) — Victory Point Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1868
msgid ""
"Two empires cooperate against incoming Doomsday Machines with Galactic "
"Capitol and Victory Point tracking."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1870
msgid ""
"8.0 Doomsday Machine Coop (2-Player) - Victory Point Rules\n"
"An evil race is sending DMs at two cooperating empires."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1873
msgid "8.1 Setup"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1875
msgid ""
"8.1.1 Homeworlds: Players place Homeworlds on \"H\" hexes. 30 CP "
"Homeworld used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1877
msgid "8.1.2 Starting Tech: Players start with Terraforming 1 and Exploration 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1879
msgid ""
"8.1.3 Turn Order: DM \"team\" always goes first unless a player spends 5 "
"CP in the bid ([MRB 7.4]). Only players that paid 5 CP may move before "
"DMs (see [1.1.10])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1881
msgid ""
"8.1.4 Special Rules: Alien Technology cards ([MRB 11.0]), Non-Player "
"Aliens ([MRB 18.0]), and Ground Units ([MRB 21.0]) may be used. NOT used:"
" Empire Advantages ([MRB 10.0]), Crew cards ([MRB 12.0]), Facilities "
"([MRB 36.0]), Ship Experience ([MRB 37.0]), Resource cards ([MRB 39.0])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1883
msgid ""
"8.1.5 Galactic Capitol: Ancient GC in center surrounded by six Nebulae. "
"Place 5 CP Colony marker. Neither player may bombard, capture, or deliver"
" Minerals to GC, but may defend it from DM attack."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1885
msgid ""
"8.1.6 Galactic Minerals: 10-Mineral counter at GC. Respawns when "
"consumed. Players split Minerals."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1887
msgid ""
"8.1.7 Warp Points: WP at GC (no counter). WP1 counter on \"WP\" space "
"between players. Both players may use at any time."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1889
msgid ""
"8.1.8 Deep Space Markers: Placed everywhere above black line except "
"around GC, in player HS, and WP spaces."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1891
msgid "8.2 Victory Conditions"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1893
msgid "8.2.1 Player Victory: Survive the DM onslaught."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1895
msgid ""
"8.2.2 DM Victory: Either player loses Homeworld, GC destroyed, or DMs "
"accumulate 10 VPs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1897
msgid ""
"8.2.3 Tracking DM VPs:\n"
"Destroyed Player Colony: +2 VPs\n"
"Destroyed NPA Planet: +2 VPs\n"
"Player colonizes/captures NPA Colony: -2 VPs"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1902
msgid "8.2.4 Deep Space Colonization: Each DS planet colonized by human = -2 VPs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1904
msgid ""
"8.3 Doomsday Machine Details\n"
"Where silent, DMs operate as in solitaire ([2.0])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1907
msgid ""
"8.3.1 Arrival Times: Per Difficulty Table ([8.7]) after players complete "
"Economic Phases."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1909
msgid ""
"8.3.2 Determine Type: Roll 1-6 Extermination DM, 7-10 Exploration DM.\n"
"Extermination DMs target Homeworlds/GC. Exploration DMs target nearest "
"Colony/NPA planet (excluding GC)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1912
msgid "8.3.3 Arrival Locations: Roll 1-4 Left, 5-6 Center, 7-10 Right."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1914
msgid ""
"8.3.4 Strength/Weakness: Strength from DM Strength Table ([8.5]). "
"Weakness from DM Weakness Table ([8.6]) on first encounter."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1916
msgid ""
"8.3.5 Movement Rate: 1 hex/turn. No Warp Points. Unexplored hexes "
"immediately revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1918
msgid ""
"8.3.6 Folds/Regional Maps/Space Pirates: DMs move through Folds normally."
" Regional Maps and Pirates removed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1920
msgid ""
"8.3.7 Danger/Lost in Space/Supernovas/Black Holes: No effect. Removed "
"immediately."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1922
msgid ""
"8.3.8 Asteroids/Nebulae/Quasars/Cosmic Storms: No effect in combat. DMs "
"don't avoid them. Don't destroy Asteroids."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1924
msgid "8.3.9 Minerals: Removed from game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1926
msgid "8.3.10 Space Wrecks: Destroyed immediately. No VP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1928
msgid ""
"8.3.11 Planets and Colonies: DM destroys planet after defeating "
"defenders. Replace with Asteroid counter. +2 VPs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1930
msgid ""
"8.3.12 DS Barren Planets: Place 4 random NPAs. NPAs fight DM. Planet "
"destroyed after = +2 VPs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1932
msgid ""
"8.3.13 Combat Behavior: Always initiate combat. Target most threatening "
"ships first."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1934
msgid "8.3.14 Damage/Healing: Carries over. +2 HP upon destroying planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1936
msgid ""
"8.3.15 Extermination DMs: Left side targets leftmost player HW. Right "
"targets rightmost. Center targets GC."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1938
msgid ""
"8.3.16 Exploration DMs: Target closest NPA planet or player Colony. Avoid"
" HW and GC. Recheck targets each Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1940
msgid "8.4 Black Hole Jumping: As per [6.4.2] with WPs as per [6.1.5]."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1942
msgid "8.5 DM Strength Table: Same as solitaire ([2.5])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1944
msgid "8.6 DM Weakness Table: Same as solitaire ([2.6])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1946
msgid ""
"8.7 DM Difficulty (2-Player):\n"
"Easy: 6/1, 7/3, 8/5, 10/7, 12/9\n"
"Normal: 6/3, 7/4, 8/6, 10/8, 12/10\n"
"Hard: 5/4, 6/5, 7/7, 9/9, 10/10\n"
"Harder: 5/5, 6/6, 7/8, 8/10, 10/8x2\n"
"Good Luck!: 5/6, 6/7, 7/9, 8/8x2, 10/9x3\n"
"\"#/#\" = Economic Phase/DM Rating. \"x2\"/\"x3\" = multiple DMs launched"
" simultaneously."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1962
msgid "Doomsday Machine Coop — Hidden Galactic Capitol Variant"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1970
msgid ""
"Variant for all DM coop scenarios. The GC counter is shuffled with random"
" Deep Space counters."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1972
msgid ""
"8.1.9 Hidden Galactic Capitol - DM Scenario Variant\n"
"Setup as per [2.9] shuffling the GC counter in with DS counters and "
"placing in the blue dot hexes. Place the WP in any non-blue dot hex "
"adjacent to one of the player home systems. Instead of using the table in"
" [8.3.3] for DM entry, roll 1d10 and place the DM on the hex matching the"
" result. All other setup is per the above scenario."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1979
msgid "Doomsday Machine Coop (3-Player) — Victory Point Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1987
msgid ""
"3-player version of the DM Coop scenario. Same rules as 2-player with "
"adjusted map and DM targeting."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1989
msgid "9.0 Doomsday Machine Coop (3-Player) - Victory Point Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1991
msgid ""
"9.1 Setup\n"
"The gameplay in this scenario is the same as in the 2-Player Doomsday "
"Machine Coop scenario except as noted below."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1994
msgid ""
"9.1.1 Deep Space Markers: Deep Space markers are placed on all white "
"hexes that are not otherwise marked."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1996
msgid "9.2 Doomsday Machine Destinations"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:1998
msgid ""
"9.2.1 Extermination DMs: Target the player Homeworld on the opposite side"
" of the board from their starting position. They avoid the Galactic "
"Capitol hex at all costs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2000
msgid ""
"9.2.2 Exploration DMs: Target whichever is nearest - a player Colony, a "
"Non-Player Alien planet, or the Galactic Capitol."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2002
msgid "9.3 Victory Conditions: Same as 2-player scenario."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2004
msgid ""
"DM Difficulty (3-Player):\n"
"Easy: 6/1, 7/3, 8/5, 10/7, 12/9\n"
"Normal: 6/3, 7/4, 8/6, 10/8, 12/10\n"
"Hard: 5/4, 6/5, 7/7, 9/9, 10/10\n"
"Harder: 5/5, 6/6, 7/8, 8/10, 10/8x2\n"
"Good Luck!: 5/6, 6/7, 7/9, 8/8x2, 10/9x3"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2015
msgid "Doomsday Machine Coop (4-Player) — Victory Point Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2023
msgid ""
"4-player version of the DM Coop scenario. GC surrounded by 3 Nebulae. "
"Adjusted DM targeting."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2025
msgid "10.0 Doomsday Machine Coop (4-Player) - Victory Point Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2027
msgid ""
"10.1 Setup\n"
"Same as 2-Player except as noted below."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2030
msgid "10.1.1 Deep Space Markers: Placed on all hexes not otherwise marked."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2032
msgid "10.1.2 Galactic Capitol: Placed as indicated, surrounded by three Nebulae."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2034
msgid "10.2 Doomsday Machine Destinations"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2036
msgid ""
"10.2.1 Extermination DMs: Left/right DMs target opposite side player with"
" least CP income. Center DMs target player with least CP income overall. "
"Ties chosen randomly. Avoid GC at all costs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2038
msgid ""
"10.2.2 Exploration DMs: Target the Galactic Capitol. Players 1 and 2 "
"particularly in danger from left/right Exploration DMs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2040
msgid ""
"10.3 DM Difficulty (4-Player):\n"
"Easy: 6/2, 7/4, 8/7, 11/9, 12/7x2\n"
"Normal: 6/3, 7/6, 8/9, 9/10, 12/9x2\n"
"Hard: 5/3, 6/5, 7/7, 9/8x2, 10/10x2\n"
"Harder: 5/4, 6/6, 7/6x2, 10/8x2, 12/9x3\n"
"Good Luck!: 5/4x2, 6/6, 7/6x2, 9/8x2, 11/10x3"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2047
msgid "10.4 Victory Conditions: Same as 2-player scenario."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2053
msgid "Alien Empire Coop (2-Player) — Victory Point Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2061
msgid "2-player cooperative version of the Solitaire Alien Empire VP scenario."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2063
msgid "11.0 Alien Empire Coop (2-Player) - Victory Point Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2065
msgid ""
"11.1 Setup\n"
"Same as solitaire section [6.0] except as noted."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2068
msgid ""
"11.1.1 Extermination Fleet Targeting: If launched during an odd numbered "
"Economic Phase, target is the Galactic Capitol. Otherwise, target nearest"
" player Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2070
msgid ""
"11.2 AP Difficulty - 2-Player COOP:\n"
"Easy: 2 APs, 5 CP/Econ, Starting Bank 150, Max Defense 50\n"
