#: app/data/scenario_list.py:2195
msgid ""
"13.6 New Hidden Galactic Capitol Rules\n"
"• These rules represent a new scenario where the GC is hidden at the "
"start. The AP Bot may be used with almost any previous scenario and does "
"not require this scenario.\n"
"• Features: The GC represents an ancient, super-advanced civilization. It"
" has a 5 CP colony counter on it. It will generate Militia if attacked "
"and will lose levels if bombarded like a Colony. It will also grow a "
"level at the end of every Econ Phase if bombarded below the 5 CP level. "
"Human players may not attack a GC but combat with the AP may occur in the"
" GC hex. Human players may place ground troops on the GC which will fight"
" alongside the GC Militia to defend against AP invasion.\n"
"• GC Discovery: The GC's location is not known at the start of the game. "
"The GC counter is seeded into an assortment of Deep Space markers "
"randomly placed near the human players. Set aside the GC counter and 9 "
"random Deep Space counters. The GC is added face down at random. If the "
"scenario has fewer than 9 DS border hexes, remove random non-GC counters "
"to match.\n"
"• Place these DS counters adjacent to your HS. If playing with more than "
"1 human player, distribute them equidistant from each HS edge. If "
"solitaire, place in the first row of DS hexes centering to your HW.\n"
"• GC Trade: Extend MS Pipelines to GC hex for 5 CP per Econ Phase "
"(instead of 1 CP). Multiple human players may benefit simultaneously. "
"Optionally replace economic gain in other GC scenarios with this rule.\n"
"• GC Loss Condition: If the GC is captured or eliminated, the Players "
"lose.\n"
"• Deep Space DMs: Never attack the Galactic Capitol."
msgstr ""
